48/* Compute variance to derive AC energy of each block */
49inline uint32_t acEnergyVar(Frame *curFrame, uint64_t sum_ssd, int shift, int plane)
50{
51 uint32_t sum = (uint32_t)sum_ssd;
52 uint32_t ssd = (uint32_t)(sum_ssd >> 32);
53
54 curFrame->m_lowres.wp_sum[plane] += sum;
55 curFrame->m_lowres.wp_ssd[plane] += ssd;
56 return ssd - ((uint64_t)sum * sum >> shift);
57}
58
59/* Find the energy of each block in Y/Cb/Cr plane */
60inline uint32_t acEnergyPlane(Frame *curFrame, pixel* src, intptr_t srcStride, int plane, int colorFormat, uint32_t qgSize)
61{
62 if ((colorFormat != X265_CSP_I444) && plane)
63 {
64 if (qgSize == 8)
65 {
66 ALIGN_VAR_4(pixel, pix[4 * 4]);
67 primitives.cu[BLOCK_4x4].copy_pp(pix, 4, src, srcStride);
68 return acEnergyVar(curFrame, primitives.cu[BLOCK_4x4].var(pix, 4), 4, plane);
69 }
70 else
71 {
72 ALIGN_VAR_8(pixel, pix[8 * 8]);
73 primitives.cu[BLOCK_8x8].copy_pp(pix, 8, src, srcStride);
74 return acEnergyVar(curFrame, primitives.cu[BLOCK_8x8].var(pix, 8), 6, plane);
75 }
76 }
77 else
78 {
79 if (qgSize == 8)
80 return acEnergyVar(curFrame, primitives.cu[BLOCK_8x8].var(src, srcStride), 6, plane);
81 else
82 return acEnergyVar(curFrame, primitives.cu[BLOCK_16x16].var(src, srcStride), 8, plane);
83 }
84}

90bool computeEdge(pixel* edgePic, pixel* refPic, pixel* edgeTheta, intptr_t stride, int height, int width, bool bcalcTheta, pixel whitePixel)
91{
92 intptr_t rowOne = 0, rowTwo = 0, rowThree = 0, colOne = 0, colTwo = 0, colThree = 0;
93 intptr_t middle = 0, topLeft = 0, topRight = 0, bottomLeft = 0, bottomRight = 0;
94
95 const int startIndex = 1;
96
97 if (!edgePic || !refPic || (!edgeTheta && bcalcTheta))
98 {
99 return false;
100 }
101 else
102 {
103 float gradientH = 0, gradientV = 0, radians = 0, theta = 0;
104 float gradientMagnitude = 0;
105 pixel blackPixel = 0;
106
107 //Applying Sobel filter expect for border pixels
108 height = height - startIndex;
109 width = width - startIndex;
110 for (int rowNum = startIndex; rowNum < height; rowNum++)
111 {
112 rowTwo = rowNum * stride;
113 rowOne = rowTwo - stride;
114 rowThree = rowTwo + stride;
115
116 for (int colNum = startIndex; colNum < width; colNum++)
117 {
118
119 /* Horizontal and vertical gradients
120 [ -3 0 3 ] [-3 -10 -3 ]
121 gH =[ -10 0 10] gV = [ 0 0 0 ]
122 [ -3 0 3 ] [ 3 10 3 ] */
123
124 colTwo = colNum;
125 colOne = colTwo - startIndex;
126 colThree = colTwo + startIndex;
127 middle = rowTwo + colTwo;
128 topLeft = rowOne + colOne;
129 topRight = rowOne + colThree;
130 bottomLeft = rowThree + colOne;
131 bottomRight = rowThree + colThree;
132 gradientH = (float)(-3 * refPic[topLeft] + 3 * refPic[topRight] - 10 * refPic[rowTwo + colOne] + 10 * refPic[rowTwo + colThree] - 3 * refPic[bottomLeft] + 3 * refPic[bottomRight]);
133 gradientV = (float)(-3 * refPic[topLeft] - 10 * refPic[rowOne + colTwo] - 3 * refPic[topRight] + 3 * refPic[bottomLeft] + 10 * refPic[rowThree + colTwo] + 3 * refPic[bottomRight]);
134 gradientMagnitude = sqrtf(gradientH * gradientH + gradientV * gradientV);
135 if(bcalcTheta)
136 {
137 edgeTheta[middle] = 0;
138 radians = atan2(gradientV, gradientH);
139 theta = (float)((radians * 180) / PI);
140 if (theta < 0)
141 theta = 180 + theta;
142 edgeTheta[middle] = (pixel)theta;
143 }
144 edgePic[middle] = (pixel)(gradientMagnitude >= EDGE_THRESHOLD ? whitePixel : blackPixel);
145 }
146 }
147 return true;
148 }
149}
150
151void edgeFilter(Frame *curFrame, x265_param* param)
152{
153 int height = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight;
154 int width = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth;
155 intptr_t stride = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride;
156 uint32_t numCuInHeight = (height + param->maxCUSize - 1) / param->maxCUSize;
157 int maxHeight = numCuInHeight * param->maxCUSize;
158
159 memset(curFrame->m_edgePic, 0, stride * (maxHeight + (curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * 2)) * sizeof(pixel));
160 memset(curFrame->m_gaussianPic, 0, stride * (maxHeight + (curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * 2)) * sizeof(pixel));
161 memset(curFrame->m_thetaPic, 0, stride * (maxHeight + (curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * 2)) * sizeof(pixel));
162
163 pixel *src = (pixel*)curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[0];
164 pixel *edgePic = curFrame->m_edgePic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
165 pixel *refPic = curFrame->m_gaussianPic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
166 pixel *edgeTheta = curFrame->m_thetaPic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
167
168 for (int i = 0; i < height; i++)
169 {
170 memcpy(edgePic, src, width * sizeof(pixel));
171 memcpy(refPic, src, width * sizeof(pixel));
172 src += stride;
173 edgePic += stride;
174 refPic += stride;
175 }
176
177 //Applying Gaussian filter on the picture
178 src = (pixel*)curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[0];
179 refPic = curFrame->m_gaussianPic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
180 edgePic = curFrame->m_edgePic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
181 pixel pixelValue = 0;
182
183 for (int rowNum = 0; rowNum < height; rowNum++)
184 {
185 for (int colNum = 0; colNum < width; colNum++)
186 {
187 if ((rowNum >= 2) && (colNum >= 2) && (rowNum != height - 2) && (colNum != width - 2)) //Ignoring the border pixels of the picture
188 {
189 /* 5x5 Gaussian filter
190 [2 4 5 4 2]
191 1 [4 9 12 9 4]
192 --- [5 12 15 12 5]
193 159 [4 9 12 9 4]
194 [2 4 5 4 2]*/
195
196 const intptr_t rowOne = (rowNum - 2)*stride, colOne = colNum - 2;
197 const intptr_t rowTwo = (rowNum - 1)*stride, colTwo = colNum - 1;
198 const intptr_t rowThree = rowNum * stride, colThree = colNum;
199 const intptr_t rowFour = (rowNum + 1)*stride, colFour = colNum + 1;
200 const intptr_t rowFive = (rowNum + 2)*stride, colFive = colNum + 2;
201 const intptr_t index = (rowNum*stride) + colNum;
202
203 pixelValue = ((2 * src[rowOne + colOne] + 4 * src[rowOne + colTwo] + 5 * src[rowOne + colThree] + 4 * src[rowOne + colFour] + 2 * src[rowOne + colFive] +
204 4 * src[rowTwo + colOne] + 9 * src[rowTwo + colTwo] + 12 * src[rowTwo + colThree] + 9 * src[rowTwo + colFour] + 4 * src[rowTwo + colFive] +
205 5 * src[rowThree + colOne] + 12 * src[rowThree + colTwo] + 15 * src[rowThree + colThree] + 12 * src[rowThree + colFour] + 5 * src[rowThree + colFive] +
206 4 * src[rowFour + colOne] + 9 * src[rowFour + colTwo] + 12 * src[rowFour + colThree] + 9 * src[rowFour + colFour] + 4 * src[rowFour + colFive] +
207 2 * src[rowFive + colOne] + 4 * src[rowFive + colTwo] + 5 * src[rowFive + colThree] + 4 * src[rowFive + colFour] + 2 * src[rowFive + colFive]) / 159);
208 refPic[index] = pixelValue;
209 }
210 }
211 }
212
213 if(!computeEdge(edgePic, refPic, edgeTheta, stride, height, width, true))
214 x265_log(NULL, X265_LOG_ERROR, "Failed edge computation!");
215}

217//Find the angle of a block by averaging the pixel angles
218inline void findAvgAngle(const pixel* block, intptr_t stride, uint32_t size, uint32_t &angle)
219{
220 int sum = 0;
221 for (uint32_t y = 0; y < size; y++)
222 {
223 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < size; x++)
224 {
225 sum += block[x];
226 }
227 block += stride;
228 }
229 angle = sum / (size*size);
230}
231
232uint32_t LookaheadTLD::edgeDensityCu(Frame* curFrame, uint32_t &avgAngle, uint32_t blockX, uint32_t blockY, uint32_t qgSize)
233{
234 pixel *edgeImage = curFrame->m_edgePic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
235 pixel *edgeTheta = curFrame->m_thetaPic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
236 intptr_t srcStride = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride;
237 intptr_t blockOffsetLuma = blockX + (blockY * srcStride);
238 int plane = 0; // Sobel filter is applied only on Y component
239 uint32_t var;
240
241 if (qgSize == 8)
242 {
243 findAvgAngle(edgeTheta + blockOffsetLuma, srcStride, qgSize, avgAngle);
244 var = acEnergyVar(curFrame, primitives.cu[BLOCK_8x8].var(edgeImage + blockOffsetLuma, srcStride), 6, plane);
245 }
246 else
247 {
248 findAvgAngle(edgeTheta + blockOffsetLuma, srcStride, 16, avgAngle);
249 var = acEnergyVar(curFrame, primitives.cu[BLOCK_16x16].var(edgeImage + blockOffsetLuma, srcStride), 8, plane);
250 }
251 x265_emms();
252 return var;
253}
254
255/* Find the total AC energy of each block in all planes */
256uint32_t LookaheadTLD::acEnergyCu(Frame* curFrame, uint32_t blockX, uint32_t blockY, int csp, uint32_t qgSize)
257{
258 intptr_t stride = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride;
259 intptr_t cStride = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_strideC;
260 intptr_t blockOffsetLuma = blockX + (blockY * stride);
261 int hShift = CHROMA_H_SHIFT(csp);
262 int vShift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT(csp);
263 intptr_t blockOffsetChroma = (blockX >> hShift) + ((blockY >> vShift) * cStride);
264
265 uint32_t var;
266
267 var = acEnergyPlane(curFrame, curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[0] + blockOffsetLuma, stride, 0, csp, qgSize);
268 if (csp != X265_CSP_I400 && curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picCsp != X265_CSP_I400)
269 {
270 var += acEnergyPlane(curFrame, curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[1] + blockOffsetChroma, cStride, 1, csp, qgSize);
271 var += acEnergyPlane(curFrame, curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[2] + blockOffsetChroma, cStride, 2, csp, qgSize);
272 }
273 x265_emms();
274 return var;
275}
276
277/* Find the sum of pixels of each block for luma plane */
278uint32_t LookaheadTLD::lumaSumCu(Frame* curFrame, uint32_t blockX, uint32_t blockY, uint32_t qgSize)
279{
280 intptr_t stride = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride;
281 intptr_t blockOffsetLuma = blockX + (blockY * stride);
282 uint64_t sum_ssd;
283
284 if (qgSize == 8)
285 sum_ssd = primitives.cu[BLOCK_8x8].var(curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[0] + blockOffsetLuma, stride);
286 else
287 sum_ssd = primitives.cu[BLOCK_16x16].var(curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[0] + blockOffsetLuma, stride);
288
289 x265_emms();
290 return (uint32_t)sum_ssd;
291}

293void LookaheadTLD::xPreanalyzeQp(Frame* curFrame)
294{
295 const uint32_t width = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth;
296 const uint32_t height = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight;
297
298 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < 4; d++)
299 {
300 int ctuSizeIdx = 6 - g_log2Size[curFrame->m_param->maxCUSize];
301 int aqDepth = g_log2Size[curFrame->m_param->maxCUSize] - g_log2Size[curFrame->m_param->rc.qgSize];
302 if (!aqLayerDepth[ctuSizeIdx][aqDepth][d])
303 continue;
304
305 PicQPAdaptationLayer* pcAQLayer = &curFrame->m_lowres.pAQLayer[d];
306 const uint32_t aqPartWidth = pcAQLayer->aqPartWidth;
307 const uint32_t aqPartHeight = pcAQLayer->aqPartHeight;
308 double* pcAQU = pcAQLayer->dActivity;
309 double* pcQP = pcAQLayer->dQpOffset;
310 double* pcCuTree = pcAQLayer->dCuTreeOffset;
311
312 for (uint32_t y = 0; y < height; y += aqPartHeight)
313 {
314 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < width; x += aqPartWidth, pcAQU++, pcQP++, pcCuTree++)
315 {
316 double dMaxQScale = pow(2.0, curFrame->m_param->rc.qpAdaptationRange / 6.0);
317 double dCUAct = *pcAQU;
318 double dAvgAct = pcAQLayer->dAvgActivity;
319
320 double dNormAct = (dMaxQScale*dCUAct + dAvgAct) / (dCUAct + dMaxQScale*dAvgAct);
321 double dQpOffset = (X265_LOG2(dNormAct) / X265_LOG2(2.0)) * 6.0;
322 *pcQP = dQpOffset;
323 *pcCuTree = dQpOffset;
324 }
325 }
326 }
327}

329void LookaheadTLD::xPreanalyze(Frame* curFrame)
330{
331 const uint32_t width = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth;
332 const uint32_t height = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight;
333 const intptr_t stride = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride;
334
335 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < 4; d++)
336 {
337 int ctuSizeIdx = 6 - g_log2Size[curFrame->m_param->maxCUSize];
338 int aqDepth = g_log2Size[curFrame->m_param->maxCUSize] - g_log2Size[curFrame->m_param->rc.qgSize];
339 if (!aqLayerDepth[ctuSizeIdx][aqDepth][d])
340 continue;
341
342 const pixel* src = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picOrg[0];;
343 PicQPAdaptationLayer* pQPLayer = &curFrame->m_lowres.pAQLayer[d];
344 const uint32_t aqPartWidth = pQPLayer->aqPartWidth;
345 const uint32_t aqPartHeight = pQPLayer->aqPartHeight;
346 double* pcAQU = pQPLayer->dActivity;
347
348 double dSumAct = 0.0;
349 for (uint32_t y = 0; y < height; y += aqPartHeight)
350 {
351 const uint32_t currAQPartHeight = X265_MIN(aqPartHeight, height - y);
352 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < width; x += aqPartWidth, pcAQU++)
353 {
354 const uint32_t currAQPartWidth = X265_MIN(aqPartWidth, width - x);
355 const pixel* pBlkY = &src[x];
356 uint64_t sum[4] = { 0, 0, 0, 0 };
357 uint64_t sumSq[4] = { 0, 0, 0, 0 };
358 uint32_t by = 0;
359 for (; by < currAQPartHeight >> 1; by++)
360 {
361 uint32_t bx = 0;
362 for (; bx < currAQPartWidth >> 1; bx++)
363 {
364 sum[0] += pBlkY[bx];
365 sumSq[0] += pBlkY[bx] * pBlkY[bx];
366 }
367 for (; bx < currAQPartWidth; bx++)
368 {
369 sum[1] += pBlkY[bx];
370 sumSq[1] += pBlkY[bx] * pBlkY[bx];
371 }
372 pBlkY += stride;
373 }
374 for (; by < currAQPartHeight; by++)
375 {
376 uint32_t bx = 0;
377 for (; bx < currAQPartWidth >> 1; bx++)
378 {
379 sum[2] += pBlkY[bx];
380 sumSq[2] += pBlkY[bx] * pBlkY[bx];
381 }
382 for (; bx < currAQPartWidth; bx++)
383 {
384 sum[3] += pBlkY[bx];
385 sumSq[3] += pBlkY[bx] * pBlkY[bx];
386 }
387 pBlkY += stride;
388 }
389
390 assert((currAQPartWidth & 1) == 0);
391 assert((currAQPartHeight & 1) == 0);
392 const uint32_t pixelWidthOfQuadrants = currAQPartWidth >> 1;
393 const uint32_t pixelHeightOfQuadrants = currAQPartHeight >> 1;
394 const uint32_t numPixInAQPart = pixelWidthOfQuadrants * pixelHeightOfQuadrants;
395
396 double dMinVar = MAX_DOUBLE;
397 if (numPixInAQPart != 0)
398 {
399 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
400 {
401 const double dAverage = double(sum[i]) / numPixInAQPart;
402 const double dVariance = double(sumSq[i]) / numPixInAQPart - dAverage * dAverage;
403 dMinVar = X265_MIN(dMinVar, dVariance);
404 }
405 }
406 else
407 {
408 dMinVar = 0.0;
409 }
410 double dActivity = 1.0 + dMinVar;
411 *pcAQU = dActivity;
412 dSumAct += dActivity;
413 }
414 src += stride * currAQPartHeight;
415 }
416
417 const double dAvgAct = dSumAct / (pQPLayer->numAQPartInWidth * pQPLayer->numAQPartInHeight);
418 pQPLayer->dAvgActivity = dAvgAct;
419 }
420
421 xPreanalyzeQp(curFrame);
422
423 int minAQDepth = curFrame->m_lowres.pAQLayer->minAQDepth;
424
425 PicQPAdaptationLayer* pQPLayer = &curFrame->m_lowres.pAQLayer[minAQDepth];
426 const uint32_t aqPartWidth = pQPLayer->aqPartWidth;
427 const uint32_t aqPartHeight = pQPLayer->aqPartHeight;
428 double* pcQP = pQPLayer->dQpOffset;
429
430 // Use new qp offset values for qpAqOffset, qpCuTreeOffset and invQscaleFactor buffer
431 int blockXY = 0;
432 for (uint32_t y = 0; y < height; y += aqPartHeight)
433 {
434 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < width; x += aqPartWidth, pcQP++)
435 {
436 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[blockXY] = x265_exp2fix8(*pcQP);
437 blockXY++;
438
439 acEnergyCu(curFrame, x, y, curFrame->m_param->internalCsp, curFrame->m_param->rc.qgSize);
440 }
441 }
442}
443
444void LookaheadTLD::calcAdaptiveQuantFrame(Frame *curFrame, x265_param* param)
445{
446 /* Actual adaptive quantization */
447 int maxCol = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth;
448 int maxRow = curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight;
449 int blockCount, loopIncr;
450 float modeOneConst, modeTwoConst;
451 if (param->rc.qgSize == 8)
452 {
453 blockCount = curFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRowFullRes * curFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInColFullRes;
454 modeOneConst = 11.427f;
455 modeTwoConst = 8.f;
456 loopIncr = 8;
457 }
458 else
459 {
460 blockCount = widthInCU * heightInCU;
461 modeOneConst = 14.427f;
462 modeTwoConst = 11.f;
463 loopIncr = 16;
464 }
465
466 float* quantOffsets = curFrame->m_quantOffsets;
467 for (int y = 0; y < 3; y++)
468 {
469 curFrame->m_lowres.wp_ssd[y] = 0;
470 curFrame->m_lowres.wp_sum[y] = 0;
471 }
472
473 if (!(param->rc.bStatRead && param->rc.cuTree && IS_REFERENCED(curFrame)))
474 {
475 /* Calculate Qp offset for each 16x16 or 8x8 block in the frame */
476 if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_NONE || param->rc.aqStrength == 0)
477 {
478 if (param->rc.aqMode && param->rc.aqStrength == 0)
479 {
480 if (quantOffsets)
481 {
482 for (int cuxy = 0; cuxy < blockCount; cuxy++)
483 {
484 curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset[cuxy] = curFrame->m_lowres.qpAqOffset[cuxy] = quantOffsets[cuxy];
485 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[cuxy] = x265_exp2fix8(curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset[cuxy]);
486 }
487 }
488 else
489 {
490 memset(curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset, 0, blockCount * sizeof(double));
491 memset(curFrame->m_lowres.qpAqOffset, 0, blockCount * sizeof(double));
492 for (int cuxy = 0; cuxy < blockCount; cuxy++)
493 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[cuxy] = 256;
494 }
495 }
496
497 /* Need variance data for weighted prediction and dynamic refinement*/
498 if (param->bEnableWeightedPred || param->bEnableWeightedBiPred)
499 {
500 for (int blockY = 0; blockY < maxRow; blockY += loopIncr)
501 for (int blockX = 0; blockX < maxCol; blockX += loopIncr)
502 acEnergyCu(curFrame, blockX, blockY, param->internalCsp, param->rc.qgSize);
503 }
504 }
505 else
506 {
507 if (param->rc.hevcAq)
508 {
509 // New method for calculating variance and qp offset
510 xPreanalyze(curFrame);
511 }
512 else
513 {
514 int blockXY = 0, inclinedEdge = 0;
515 double avg_adj_pow2 = 0, avg_adj = 0, qp_adj = 0;
516 double bias_strength = 0.f;
517 double strength = 0.f;
518
519 if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_EDGE)
520 edgeFilter(curFrame, param);
521
522 if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_EDGE && !param->bHistBasedSceneCut && param->recursionSkipMode == EDGE_BASED_RSKIP)
523 {
524 pixel* src = curFrame->m_edgePic + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginY * curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride + curFrame->m_fencPic->m_lumaMarginX;
525 primitives.planecopy_pp_shr(src, curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride, curFrame->m_edgeBitPic,
526 curFrame->m_fencPic->m_stride, curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picWidth, curFrame->m_fencPic->m_picHeight, SHIFT_TO_BITPLANE);
527 }
528
529 if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_AUTO_VARIANCE || param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_AUTO_VARIANCE_BIASED || param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_EDGE)
530 {
531 double bit_depth_correction = 1.f / (1 << (2 * (X265_DEPTH - 8)));
532 for (int blockY = 0; blockY < maxRow; blockY += loopIncr)
533 {
534 for (int blockX = 0; blockX < maxCol; blockX += loopIncr)
535 {
536 uint32_t energy, edgeDensity, avgAngle;
537 energy = acEnergyCu(curFrame, blockX, blockY, param->internalCsp, param->rc.qgSize);
538 if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_EDGE)
539 {
540 edgeDensity = edgeDensityCu(curFrame, avgAngle, blockX, blockY, param->rc.qgSize);
541 if (edgeDensity)
542 {
543 qp_adj = pow(edgeDensity * bit_depth_correction + 1, 0.1);
544 //Increasing the QP of a block if its edge orientation lies around the multiples of 45 degree
545 if ((avgAngle >= EDGE_INCLINATION - 15 && avgAngle <= EDGE_INCLINATION + 15) || (avgAngle >= EDGE_INCLINATION + 75 && avgAngle <= EDGE_INCLINATION + 105))
546 curFrame->m_lowres.edgeInclined[blockXY] = 1;
547 else
548 curFrame->m_lowres.edgeInclined[blockXY] = 0;
549 }
550 else
551 {
552 qp_adj = pow(energy * bit_depth_correction + 1, 0.1);
553 curFrame->m_lowres.edgeInclined[blockXY] = 0;
554 }
555 }
556 else
557 qp_adj = pow(energy * bit_depth_correction + 1, 0.1);
558 curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset[blockXY] = qp_adj;
559 avg_adj += qp_adj;
560 avg_adj_pow2 += qp_adj * qp_adj;
561 blockXY++;
562 }
563 }
564 avg_adj /= blockCount;
565 avg_adj_pow2 /= blockCount;
566 strength = param->rc.aqStrength * avg_adj;
567 avg_adj = avg_adj - 0.5f * (avg_adj_pow2 - modeTwoConst) / avg_adj;
568 bias_strength = param->rc.aqStrength;
569 }
570 else
571 strength = param->rc.aqStrength * 1.0397f;
572
573 blockXY = 0;
574 for (int blockY = 0; blockY < maxRow; blockY += loopIncr)
575 {
576 for (int blockX = 0; blockX < maxCol; blockX += loopIncr)
577 {
578 if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_AUTO_VARIANCE_BIASED)
579 {
580 qp_adj = curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset[blockXY];
581 qp_adj = strength * (qp_adj - avg_adj) + bias_strength * (1.f - modeTwoConst / (qp_adj * qp_adj));
582 }
583 else if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_AUTO_VARIANCE)
584 {
585 qp_adj = curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset[blockXY];
586 qp_adj = strength * (qp_adj - avg_adj);
587 }
588 else if (param->rc.aqMode == X265_AQ_EDGE)
589 {
590 inclinedEdge = curFrame->m_lowres.edgeInclined[blockXY];
591 qp_adj = curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset[blockXY];
592 if(inclinedEdge && (qp_adj - avg_adj > 0))
593 qp_adj = ((strength + AQ_EDGE_BIAS) * (qp_adj - avg_adj));
594 else
595 qp_adj = strength * (qp_adj - avg_adj);
596 }
597 else
598 {
599 uint32_t energy = acEnergyCu(curFrame, blockX, blockY, param->internalCsp, param->rc.qgSize);
600 qp_adj = strength * (X265_LOG2(X265_MAX(energy, 1)) - (modeOneConst + 2 * (X265_DEPTH - 8)));
601 }
602
603 if (param->bHDR10Opt)
604 {
605 uint32_t sum = lumaSumCu(curFrame, blockX, blockY, param->rc.qgSize);
606 uint32_t lumaAvg = sum / (loopIncr * loopIncr);
607 if (lumaAvg < 301)
608 qp_adj += 3;
609 else if (lumaAvg >= 301 && lumaAvg < 367)
610 qp_adj += 2;
611 else if (lumaAvg >= 367 && lumaAvg < 434)
612 qp_adj += 1;
613 else if (lumaAvg >= 501 && lumaAvg < 567)
614 qp_adj -= 1;
615 else if (lumaAvg >= 567 && lumaAvg < 634)
616 qp_adj -= 2;
617 else if (lumaAvg >= 634 && lumaAvg < 701)
618 qp_adj -= 3;
619 else if (lumaAvg >= 701 && lumaAvg < 767)
620 qp_adj -= 4;
621 else if (lumaAvg >= 767 && lumaAvg < 834)
622 qp_adj -= 5;
623 else if (lumaAvg >= 834)
624 qp_adj -= 6;
625 }
626 if (quantOffsets != NULL)
627 qp_adj += quantOffsets[blockXY];
628 curFrame->m_lowres.qpAqOffset[blockXY] = qp_adj;
629 curFrame->m_lowres.qpCuTreeOffset[blockXY] = qp_adj;
630 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[blockXY] = x265_exp2fix8(qp_adj);
631 blockXY++;
632 }
633 }
634 }
635 }
636
637 if (param->rc.qgSize == 8)
638 {
639 for (int cuY = 0; cuY < heightInCU; cuY++)
640 {
641 for (int cuX = 0; cuX < widthInCU; cuX++)
642 {
643 const int cuXY = cuX + cuY * widthInCU;
644 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor8x8[cuXY] = (curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[cuX * 2 + cuY * widthInCU * 4] +
645 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[cuX * 2 + cuY * widthInCU * 4 + 1] +
646 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[cuX * 2 + cuY * widthInCU * 4 + curFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRowFullRes] +
647 curFrame->m_lowres.invQscaleFactor[cuX * 2 + cuY * widthInCU * 4 + curFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRowFullRes + 1]) / 4;
648 }
649 }
650 }
651 }
652
653 if (param->bEnableWeightedPred || param->bEnableWeightedBiPred)
654 {
655 if (param->rc.bStatRead && param->rc.cuTree && IS_REFERENCED(curFrame))
656 {
657 for (int blockY = 0; blockY < maxRow; blockY += loopIncr)
658 for (int blockX = 0; blockX < maxCol; blockX += loopIncr)
659 acEnergyCu(curFrame, blockX, blockY, param->internalCsp, param->rc.qgSize);
660 }
661
662 int hShift = CHROMA_H_SHIFT(param->internalCsp);
663 int vShift = CHROMA_V_SHIFT(param->internalCsp);
664 maxCol = ((maxCol + 8) >> 4) << 4;
665 maxRow = ((maxRow + 8) >> 4) << 4;
666 int width[3] = { maxCol, maxCol >> hShift, maxCol >> hShift };
667 int height[3] = { maxRow, maxRow >> vShift, maxRow >> vShift };
668
669 for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++)
670 {
671 uint64_t sum, ssd;
672 sum = curFrame->m_lowres.wp_sum[i];
673 ssd = curFrame->m_lowres.wp_ssd[i];
674 curFrame->m_lowres.wp_ssd[i] = ssd - (sum * sum + (width[i] * height[i]) / 2) / (width[i] * height[i]);
675 }
676 }
677
678 if (param->bDynamicRefine || param->bEnableFades)
679 {
680 uint64_t blockXY = 0, rowVariance = 0;
681 curFrame->m_lowres.frameVariance = 0;
682 for (int blockY = 0; blockY < maxRow; blockY += loopIncr)
683 {
684 for (int blockX = 0; blockX < maxCol; blockX += loopIncr)
685 {
686 curFrame->m_lowres.blockVariance[blockXY] = acEnergyCu(curFrame, blockX, blockY, param->internalCsp, param->rc.qgSize);
687 rowVariance += curFrame->m_lowres.blockVariance[blockXY];
688 blockXY++;
689 }
690 curFrame->m_lowres.frameVariance += (rowVariance / maxCol);
691 }
692 curFrame->m_lowres.frameVariance /= maxRow;
693 }
694}
695
696void LookaheadTLD::lowresIntraEstimate(Lowres& fenc, uint32_t qgSize)
697{
698 ALIGN_VAR_32(pixel, prediction[X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE * X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE]);
699 pixel fencIntra[X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE * X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE];
700 pixel neighbours[2][X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE * 4 + 1];
701 pixel* samples = neighbours[0], *filtered = neighbours[1];
702
703 const int lookAheadLambda = (int)x265_lambda_tab[X265_LOOKAHEAD_QP];
704 const int intraPenalty = 5 * lookAheadLambda;
705 const int lowresPenalty = 4; /* fixed CU cost overhead */
706
707 const int cuSize = X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE;
708 const int cuSize2 = cuSize << 1;
709 const int sizeIdx = X265_LOWRES_CU_BITS - 2;
710
711 pixelcmp_t satd = primitives.pu[sizeIdx].satd;
712 int planar = !!(cuSize >= 8);
713
714 int costEst = 0, costEstAq = 0;
715
716 for (int cuY = 0; cuY < heightInCU; cuY++)
717 {
718 fenc.rowSatds[0][0][cuY] = 0;
719
720 for (int cuX = 0; cuX < widthInCU; cuX++)
721 {
722 const int cuXY = cuX + cuY * widthInCU;
723 const intptr_t pelOffset = cuSize * cuX + cuSize * cuY * fenc.lumaStride;
724 pixel *pixCur = fenc.lowresPlane[0] + pelOffset;
725
726 /* copy fenc pixels */
727 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].copy_pp(fencIntra, cuSize, pixCur, fenc.lumaStride);
728
729 /* collect reference sample pixels */
730 pixCur -= fenc.lumaStride + 1;
731 memcpy(samples, pixCur, (2 * cuSize + 1) * sizeof(pixel)); /* top */
732 for (int i = 1; i <= 2 * cuSize; i++)
733 samples[cuSize2 + i] = pixCur[i * fenc.lumaStride]; /* left */
734
735 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_filter(samples, filtered);
736
737 int cost, icost = me.COST_MAX;
738 uint32_t ilowmode = 0;
739
740 /* DC and planar */
741 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[DC_IDX](prediction, cuSize, samples, 0, cuSize <= 16);
742 cost = satd(fencIntra, cuSize, prediction, cuSize);
743 COPY2_IF_LT(icost, cost, ilowmode, DC_IDX);
744
745 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[PLANAR_IDX](prediction, cuSize, neighbours[planar], 0, 0);
746 cost = satd(fencIntra, cuSize, prediction, cuSize);
747 COPY2_IF_LT(icost, cost, ilowmode, PLANAR_IDX);
748
749 /* scan angular predictions */
750 int filter, acost = me.COST_MAX;
751 uint32_t mode, alowmode = 4;
752 for (mode = 5; mode < 35; mode += 5)
753 {
754 filter = !!(g_intraFilterFlags[mode] & cuSize);
755 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[mode](prediction, cuSize, neighbours[filter], mode, cuSize <= 16);
756 cost = satd(fencIntra, cuSize, prediction, cuSize);
757 COPY2_IF_LT(acost, cost, alowmode, mode);
758 }
759 for (uint32_t dist = 2; dist >= 1; dist--)
760 {
761 int minusmode = alowmode - dist;
762 int plusmode = alowmode + dist;
763
764 mode = minusmode;
765 filter = !!(g_intraFilterFlags[mode] & cuSize);
766 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[mode](prediction, cuSize, neighbours[filter], mode, cuSize <= 16);
767 cost = satd(fencIntra, cuSize, prediction, cuSize);
768 COPY2_IF_LT(acost, cost, alowmode, mode);
769
770 mode = plusmode;
771 filter = !!(g_intraFilterFlags[mode] & cuSize);
772 primitives.cu[sizeIdx].intra_pred[mode](prediction, cuSize, neighbours[filter], mode, cuSize <= 16);
773 cost = satd(fencIntra, cuSize, prediction, cuSize);
774 COPY2_IF_LT(acost, cost, alowmode, mode);
775 }
776 COPY2_IF_LT(icost, acost, ilowmode, alowmode);
777
778 icost += intraPenalty + lowresPenalty; /* estimate intra signal cost */
779
780 fenc.lowresCosts[0][0][cuXY] = (uint16_t)(X265_MIN(icost, LOWRES_COST_MASK) | (0 << LOWRES_COST_SHIFT));
781 fenc.intraCost[cuXY] = icost;
782 fenc.intraMode[cuXY] = (uint8_t)ilowmode;
783 /* do not include edge blocks in the
784 frame cost estimates, they are not very accurate */
785 const bool bFrameScoreCU = (cuX > 0 && cuX < widthInCU - 1 &&
786 cuY > 0 && cuY < heightInCU - 1) || widthInCU <= 2 || heightInCU <= 2;
787 int icostAq;
788 if (qgSize == 8)
789 icostAq = (bFrameScoreCU && fenc.invQscaleFactor) ? ((icost * fenc.invQscaleFactor8x8[cuXY] + 128) >> 8) : icost;
790 else
791 icostAq = (bFrameScoreCU && fenc.invQscaleFactor) ? ((icost * fenc.invQscaleFactor[cuXY] +128) >> 8) : icost;
792
793 if (bFrameScoreCU)
794 {
795 costEst += icost;
796 costEstAq += icostAq;
797 }
798
799 fenc.rowSatds[0][0][cuY] += icostAq;
800 }
801 }
802
803 fenc.costEst[0][0] = costEst;
804 fenc.costEstAq[0][0] = costEstAq;
805}
806
807uint32_t LookaheadTLD::weightCostLuma(Lowres& fenc, Lowres& ref, WeightParam& wp)
808{
809 pixel *src = ref.fpelPlane[0];
810 intptr_t stride = fenc.lumaStride;
811
812 if (wp.wtPresent)
813 {
814 int offset = wp.inputOffset << (X265_DEPTH - 8);
815 int scale = wp.inputWeight;
816 int denom = wp.log2WeightDenom;
817 int round = denom ? 1 << (denom - 1) : 0;
818 int correction = IF_INTERNAL_PREC - X265_DEPTH; // intermediate interpolation depth
819 int widthHeight = (int)stride;
820
821 primitives.weight_pp(ref.buffer[0], wbuffer[0], stride, widthHeight, paddedLines,
822 scale, round << correction, denom + correction, offset);
823 src = fenc.weightedRef[fenc.frameNum - ref.frameNum].fpelPlane[0];
824 }
825
826 uint32_t cost = 0;
827 intptr_t pixoff = 0;
828 int mb = 0;
829
830 for (int y = 0; y < fenc.lines; y += 8, pixoff = y * stride)
831 {
832 for (int x = 0; x < fenc.width; x += 8, mb++, pixoff += 8)
833 {
834 int satd = primitives.pu[LUMA_8x8].satd(src + pixoff, stride, fenc.fpelPlane[0] + pixoff, stride);
835 cost += X265_MIN(satd, fenc.intraCost[mb]);
836 }
837 }
838
839 return cost;
840}
841
842bool LookaheadTLD::allocWeightedRef(Lowres& fenc)
843{
844 intptr_t planesize = fenc.buffer[1] - fenc.buffer[0];
845 paddedLines = (int)(planesize / fenc.lumaStride);
846
847 wbuffer[0] = X265_MALLOC(pixel, 4 * planesize);
848 if (wbuffer[0])
849 {
850 wbuffer[1] = wbuffer[0] + planesize;
851 wbuffer[2] = wbuffer[1] + planesize;
852 wbuffer[3] = wbuffer[2] + planesize;
853 }
854 else
855 return false;
856
857 return true;
858}
859
860void LookaheadTLD::weightsAnalyse(Lowres& fenc, Lowres& ref)
861{
862 static const float epsilon = 1.f / 128.f;
863 int deltaIndex = fenc.frameNum - ref.frameNum;
864
865 WeightParam wp;
866 wp.wtPresent = 0;
867
868 if (!wbuffer[0])
869 {
870 if (!allocWeightedRef(fenc))
871 return;
872 }
873
874 ReferencePlanes& weightedRef = fenc.weightedRef[deltaIndex];
875 intptr_t padoffset = fenc.lowresPlane[0] - fenc.buffer[0];
876 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
877 weightedRef.lowresPlane[i] = wbuffer[i] + padoffset;
878
879 weightedRef.fpelPlane[0] = weightedRef.lowresPlane[0];
880 weightedRef.lumaStride = fenc.lumaStride;
881 weightedRef.isLowres = true;
882 weightedRef.isWeighted = false;
883 weightedRef.isHMELowres = ref.bEnableHME;
884
885 /* epsilon is chosen to require at least a numerator of 127 (with denominator = 128) */
886 float guessScale, fencMean, refMean;
887 x265_emms();
888 if (fenc.wp_ssd[0] && ref.wp_ssd[0])
889 guessScale = sqrtf((float)fenc.wp_ssd[0] / ref.wp_ssd[0]);
890 else
891 guessScale = 1.0f;
892 fencMean = (float)fenc.wp_sum[0] / (fenc.lines * fenc.width) / (1 << (X265_DEPTH - 8));
893 refMean = (float)ref.wp_sum[0] / (fenc.lines * fenc.width) / (1 << (X265_DEPTH - 8));
894
895 /* Early termination */
896 if (fabsf(refMean - fencMean) < 0.5f && fabsf(1.f - guessScale) < epsilon)
897 return;
898
899 int minoff = 0, minscale, mindenom;
900 unsigned int minscore = 0, origscore = 1;
901 int found = 0;
902
903 wp.setFromWeightAndOffset((int)(guessScale * 128 + 0.5f), 0, 7, true);
904 mindenom = wp.log2WeightDenom;
905 minscale = wp.inputWeight;
906
907 origscore = minscore = weightCostLuma(fenc, ref, wp);
908
909 if (!minscore)
910 return;
911
912 unsigned int s = 0;
913 int curScale = minscale;
914 int curOffset = (int)(fencMean - refMean * curScale / (1 << mindenom) + 0.5f);
915 if (curOffset < -128 || curOffset > 127)
916 {
917 /* Rescale considering the constraints on curOffset. We do it in this order
918 * because scale has a much wider range than offset (because of denom), so
919 * it should almost never need to be clamped. */
920 curOffset = x265_clip3(-128, 127, curOffset);
921 curScale = (int)((1 << mindenom) * (fencMean - curOffset) / refMean + 0.5f);
922 curScale = x265_clip3(0, 127, curScale);
923 }
924 SET_WEIGHT(wp, true, curScale, mindenom, curOffset);
925 s = weightCostLuma(fenc, ref, wp);
926 COPY4_IF_LT(minscore, s, minscale, curScale, minoff, curOffset, found, 1);
927
928 /* Use a smaller denominator if possible */
929 if (mindenom > 0 && !(minscale & 1))
930 {
931 unsigned long idx;
932 CTZ(idx, minscale);
933 int shift = X265_MIN((int)idx, mindenom);
934 mindenom -= shift;
935 minscale >>= shift;
936 }
937
938 if (!found || (minscale == 1 << mindenom && minoff == 0) || (float)minscore / origscore > 0.998f)
939 return;
940 else
941 {
942 SET_WEIGHT(wp, true, minscale, mindenom, minoff);
943
944 // set weighted delta cost
945 fenc.weightedCostDelta[deltaIndex] = minscore / origscore;
946
947 int offset = wp.inputOffset << (X265_DEPTH - 8);
948 int scale = wp.inputWeight;
949 int denom = wp.log2WeightDenom;
950 int round = denom ? 1 << (denom - 1) : 0;
951 int correction = IF_INTERNAL_PREC - X265_DEPTH; // intermediate interpolation depth
952 intptr_t stride = ref.lumaStride;
953 int widthHeight = (int)stride;
954
955 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
956 primitives.weight_pp(ref.buffer[i], wbuffer[i], stride, widthHeight, paddedLines,
957 scale, round << correction, denom + correction, offset);
958
959 weightedRef.isWeighted = true;
960 }
961}
962
963Lookahead::Lookahead(x265_param *param, ThreadPool* pool)
964{
965 m_param = param;
966 m_pool = pool;
967
968 m_lastNonB = NULL;
969 m_isSceneTransition = false;
970 m_scratch = NULL;
971 m_tld = NULL;
972 m_filled = false;
973 m_outputSignalRequired = false;
974 m_isActive = true;
975 m_inputCount = 0;
976 m_extendGopBoundary = false;
977 m_8x8Height = ((m_param->sourceHeight / 2) + X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE - 1) >> X265_LOWRES_CU_BITS;
978 m_8x8Width = ((m_param->sourceWidth / 2) + X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE - 1) >> X265_LOWRES_CU_BITS;
979 m_4x4Height = ((m_param->sourceHeight / 4) + X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE - 1) >> X265_LOWRES_CU_BITS;
980 m_4x4Width = ((m_param->sourceWidth / 4) + X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE - 1) >> X265_LOWRES_CU_BITS;
981 m_cuCount = m_8x8Width * m_8x8Height;
982 m_8x8Blocks = m_8x8Width > 2 && m_8x8Height > 2 ? (m_cuCount + 4 - 2 * (m_8x8Width + m_8x8Height)) : m_cuCount;
983 m_isFadeIn = false;
984 m_fadeCount = 0;
985 m_fadeStart = -1;
986
987 /* Allow the strength to be adjusted via qcompress, since the two concepts
988 * are very similar. */
989 m_cuTreeStrength = (m_param->rc.hevcAq ? 6.0 : 5.0) * (1.0 - m_param->rc.qCompress);
990
991 m_lastKeyframe = -m_param->keyframeMax;
992 m_sliceTypeBusy = false;
993 m_fullQueueSize = X265_MAX(1, m_param->lookaheadDepth);
994 m_bAdaptiveQuant = m_param->rc.aqMode ||
995 m_param->bEnableWeightedPred ||
996 m_param->bEnableWeightedBiPred ||
997 m_param->bAQMotion ||
998 m_param->rc.hevcAq;
999
1000 /* If we have a thread pool and are using --b-adapt 2, it is generally
1001 * preferable to perform all motion searches for each lowres frame in large
1002 * batched; this will create one job per --bframe per lowres frame, and
1003 * these jobs are performed by workers bonded to the thread running
1004 * slicetypeDecide() */
1005 m_bBatchMotionSearch = m_pool && m_param->bFrameAdaptive == X265_B_ADAPT_TRELLIS;
1006
1007 /* It is also beneficial to pre-calculate all possible frame cost estimates
1008 * using worker threads bonded to the worker thread running
1009 * slicetypeDecide(). This creates bframes * bframes jobs which take less
1010 * time than the motion search batches but there are many of them. This may
1011 * do much unnecessary work, some frame cost estimates are not needed, so if
1012 * the thread pool is small we disable this feature after the initial burst
1013 * of work */
1014 m_bBatchFrameCosts = m_bBatchMotionSearch;
1015
1016 if (m_param->lookaheadSlices && !m_pool)
1017 {
1018 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "No pools found; disabling lookahead-slices\n");
1019 m_param->lookaheadSlices = 0;
1020 }
1021
1022 if (m_param->lookaheadSlices && (m_param->sourceHeight < 720))
1023 {
1024 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Source height < 720p; disabling lookahead-slices\n");
1025 m_param->lookaheadSlices = 0;
1026 }
1027
1028 if (m_param->lookaheadSlices > 1)
1029 {
1030 m_numRowsPerSlice = m_8x8Height / m_param->lookaheadSlices;
1031 m_numRowsPerSlice = X265_MAX(m_numRowsPerSlice, 10); // at least 10 rows per slice
1032 m_numRowsPerSlice = X265_MIN(m_numRowsPerSlice, m_8x8Height); // but no more than the full picture
1033 m_numCoopSlices = m_8x8Height / m_numRowsPerSlice;
1034 m_param->lookaheadSlices = m_numCoopSlices; // report actual final slice count
1035 }
1036 else
1037 {
1038 m_numRowsPerSlice = m_8x8Height;
1039 m_numCoopSlices = 1;
1040 }
1041 if (param->gopLookahead && (param->gopLookahead > (param->lookaheadDepth - param->bframes - 2)))
1042 {
1043 param->gopLookahead = X265_MAX(0, param->lookaheadDepth - param->bframes - 2);
1044 x265_log(param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "Gop-lookahead cannot be greater than (rc-lookahead - length of the mini-gop); Clipping gop-lookahead to %d\n", param->gopLookahead);
1045 }
1046#if DETAILED_CU_STATS
1047 m_slicetypeDecideElapsedTime = 0;
1048 m_preLookaheadElapsedTime = 0;
1049 m_countSlicetypeDecide = 0;
1050 m_countPreLookahead = 0;
1051#endif
1052
1053 memset(m_histogram, 0, sizeof(m_histogram));
1054}
1055
1056#if DETAILED_CU_STATS
1057void Lookahead::getWorkerStats(int64_t& batchElapsedTime, uint64_t& batchCount, int64_t& coopSliceElapsedTime, uint64_t& coopSliceCount)
1058{
1059 batchElapsedTime = coopSliceElapsedTime = 0;
1060 coopSliceCount = batchCount = 0;
1061 int tldCount = m_pool ? m_pool->m_numWorkers : 1;
1062 for (int i = 0; i < tldCount; i++)
1063 {
1064 batchElapsedTime += m_tld[i].batchElapsedTime;
1065 coopSliceElapsedTime += m_tld[i].coopSliceElapsedTime;
1066 batchCount += m_tld[i].countBatches;
1067 coopSliceCount += m_tld[i].countCoopSlices;
1068 }
1069}
1070#endif
1071
1072bool Lookahead::create()
1073{
1074 int numTLD = 1 + (m_pool ? m_pool->m_numWorkers : 0);
1075 m_tld = new LookaheadTLD[numTLD];
1076 for (int i = 0; i < numTLD; i++)
1077 m_tld[i].init(m_8x8Width, m_8x8Height, m_8x8Blocks);
1078 m_scratch = X265_MALLOC(int, m_tld[0].widthInCU);
1079
1080 return m_tld && m_scratch;
1081}
1082
1083void Lookahead::stopJobs()
1084{
1085 if (m_pool && !m_inputQueue.empty())
1086 {
1087 m_inputLock.acquire();
1088 m_isActive = false;
1089 bool wait = m_outputSignalRequired = m_sliceTypeBusy;
1090 m_inputLock.release();
1091
1092 if (wait)
1093 m_outputSignal.wait();
1094 }
1095 if (m_pool && m_param->lookaheadThreads > 0)
1096 {
1097 for (int i = 0; i < m_numPools; i++)
1098 m_pool[i].stopWorkers();
1099 }
1100}
1101void Lookahead::destroy()
1102{
1103 // these two queues will be empty unless the encode was aborted
1104 while (!m_inputQueue.empty())
1105 {
1106 Frame* curFrame = m_inputQueue.popFront();
1107 curFrame->destroy();
1108 delete curFrame;
1109 }
1110
1111 while (!m_outputQueue.empty())
1112 {
1113 Frame* curFrame = m_outputQueue.popFront();
1114 curFrame->destroy();
1115 delete curFrame;
1116 }
1117
1118 X265_FREE(m_scratch);
1119 delete [] m_tld;
1120 if (m_param->lookaheadThreads > 0)
1121 delete [] m_pool;
1122}
1123/* The synchronization of slicetypeDecide is managed here. The findJob() method
1124 * polls the occupancy of the input queue. If the queue is
1125 * full, it will run slicetypeDecide() and output a mini-gop of frames to the
1126 * output queue. If the flush() method has been called (implying no new pictures
1127 * will be received) then the input queue is considered full if it has even one
1128 * picture left. getDecidedPicture() removes pictures from the output queue and
1129 * only blocks as a last resort. It does not start removing pictures until
1130 * m_filled is true, which occurs after *more than* the lookahead depth of
1131 * pictures have been input so slicetypeDecide() should have started prior to
1132 * output pictures being withdrawn. The first slicetypeDecide() will obviously
1133 * still require a blocking wait, but after this slicetypeDecide() will maintain
1134 * its lead over the encoder (because one picture is added to the input queue
1135 * each time one is removed from the output) and decides slice types of pictures
1136 * just ahead of when the encoder needs them */
1137
1138/* Called by API thread */
1139void Lookahead::addPicture(Frame& curFrame, int sliceType)
1140{
1141 if (m_param->analysisLoad && m_param->bDisableLookahead)
1142 {
1143 if (!m_filled)
1144 m_filled = true;
1145 m_outputLock.acquire();
1146 m_outputQueue.pushBack(curFrame);
1147 m_outputLock.release();
1148 m_inputCount++;
1149 }
1150 else
1151 {
1152 checkLookaheadQueue(m_inputCount);
1153 curFrame.m_lowres.sliceType = sliceType;
1154 addPicture(curFrame);
1155 }
1156}
1157
1158void Lookahead::addPicture(Frame& curFrame)
1159{
1160 m_inputLock.acquire();
1161 m_inputQueue.pushBack(curFrame);
1162 m_inputLock.release();
1163 m_inputCount++;
1164}
1165
1166void Lookahead::checkLookaheadQueue(int &frameCnt)
1167{
1168 /* determine if the lookahead is (over) filled enough for frames to begin to
1169 * be consumed by frame encoders */
1170 if (!m_filled)
1171 {
1172 if (!m_param->bframes & !m_param->lookaheadDepth)
1173 m_filled = true; /* zero-latency */
1174 else if (frameCnt >= m_param->lookaheadDepth + 2 + m_param->bframes)
1175 m_filled = true; /* full capacity plus mini-gop lag */
1176 }
1177
1178 m_inputLock.acquire();
1179 if (m_pool && m_inputQueue.size() >= m_fullQueueSize)
1180 tryWakeOne();
1181 m_inputLock.release();
1182}
1183
1184/* Called by API thread */
1185void Lookahead::flush()
1186{
1187 /* force slicetypeDecide to run until the input queue is empty */
1188 m_fullQueueSize = 1;
1189 m_filled = true;
1190}
1191
1192void Lookahead::setLookaheadQueue()
1193{
1194 m_filled = false;
1195 m_fullQueueSize = X265_MAX(1, m_param->lookaheadDepth);
1196}
1197
1198void Lookahead::findJob(int /*workerThreadID*/)
1199{
1200 bool doDecide;
1201
1202 m_inputLock.acquire();
1203 if (m_inputQueue.size() >= m_fullQueueSize && !m_sliceTypeBusy && m_isActive)
1204 doDecide = m_sliceTypeBusy = true;
1205 else
1206 doDecide = m_helpWanted = false;
1207 m_inputLock.release();
1208
1209 if (!doDecide)
1210 return;
1211
1212 ProfileLookaheadTime(m_slicetypeDecideElapsedTime, m_countSlicetypeDecide);
1213 ProfileScopeEvent(slicetypeDecideEV);
1214
1215 slicetypeDecide();
1216
1217 m_inputLock.acquire();
1218 if (m_outputSignalRequired)
1219 {
1220 m_outputSignal.trigger();
1221 m_outputSignalRequired = false;
1222 }
1223 m_sliceTypeBusy = false;
1224 m_inputLock.release();
1225}
1226
1227/* Called by API thread */
1228Frame* Lookahead::getDecidedPicture()
1229{
1230 if (m_filled)
1231 {
1232 m_outputLock.acquire();
1233 Frame *out = m_outputQueue.popFront();
1234 m_outputLock.release();
1235
1236 if (out)
1237 {
1238 m_inputCount--;
1239 return out;
1240 }
1241
1242 if (m_param->analysisLoad && m_param->bDisableLookahead)
1243 return NULL;
1244
1245 findJob(-1); /* run slicetypeDecide() if necessary */
1246
1247 m_inputLock.acquire();
1248 bool wait = m_outputSignalRequired = m_sliceTypeBusy;
1249 m_inputLock.release();
1250
1251 if (wait)
1252 m_outputSignal.wait();
1253
1254 out = m_outputQueue.popFront();
1255 if (out)
1256 m_inputCount--;
1257 return out;
1258 }
1259 else
1260 return NULL;
1261}
1262
1263/* Called by rate-control to calculate the estimated SATD cost for a given
1264 * picture. It assumes dpb->prepareEncode() has already been called for the
1265 * picture and all the references are established */
1266void Lookahead::getEstimatedPictureCost(Frame *curFrame)
1267{
1268 Lowres *frames[X265_LOOKAHEAD_MAX];
1269
1270 // POC distances to each reference
1271 Slice *slice = curFrame->m_encData->m_slice;
1272 int p0 = 0, p1, b;
1273 int poc = slice->m_poc;
1274 int l0poc = slice->m_rps.numberOfNegativePictures ? slice->m_refPOCList[0][0] : -1;
1275 int l1poc = slice->m_refPOCList[1][0];
1276
1277 switch (slice->m_sliceType)
1278 {
1279 case I_SLICE:
1280 frames[p0] = &curFrame->m_lowres;
1281 b = p1 = 0;
1282 break;
1283
1284 case P_SLICE:
1285 b = p1 = poc - l0poc;
1286 frames[p0] = &slice->m_refFrameList[0][0]->m_lowres;
1287 frames[b] = &curFrame->m_lowres;
1288 break;
1289
1290 case B_SLICE:
1291 if (l0poc >= 0)
1292 {
1293 b = poc - l0poc;
1294 p1 = b + l1poc - poc;
1295 frames[p0] = &slice->m_refFrameList[0][0]->m_lowres;
1296 frames[b] = &curFrame->m_lowres;
1297 frames[p1] = &slice->m_refFrameList[1][0]->m_lowres;
1298 }
1299 else
1300 {
1301 p0 = b = 0;
1302 p1 = b + l1poc - poc;
1303 frames[p0] = frames[b] = &curFrame->m_lowres;
1304 frames[p1] = &slice->m_refFrameList[1][0]->m_lowres;
1305 }
1306
1307 break;
1308
1309 default:
1310 return;
1311 }
1312 if (!m_param->analysisLoad || !m_param->bDisableLookahead)
1313 {
1314 X265_CHECK(curFrame->m_lowres.costEst[b - p0][p1 - b] > 0, "Slice cost not estimated\n")
1315
1316 if (m_param->rc.cuTree && !m_param->rc.bStatRead)
1317 /* update row satds based on cutree offsets */
1318 curFrame->m_lowres.satdCost = frameCostRecalculate(frames, p0, p1, b);
1319 else if (!m_param->analysisLoad || m_param->scaleFactor || m_param->bAnalysisType == HEVC_INFO)
1320 {
1321 if (m_param->rc.aqMode)
1322 curFrame->m_lowres.satdCost = curFrame->m_lowres.costEstAq[b - p0][p1 - b];
1323 else
1324 curFrame->m_lowres.satdCost = curFrame->m_lowres.costEst[b - p0][p1 - b];
1325 }
1326 if (m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize && m_param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate)
1327 {
1328 /* aggregate lowres row satds to CTU resolution */
1329 curFrame->m_lowres.lowresCostForRc = curFrame->m_lowres.lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b];
1330 uint32_t lowresRow = 0, lowresCol = 0, lowresCuIdx = 0, sum = 0, intraSum = 0;
1331 uint32_t scale = m_param->maxCUSize / (2 * X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE);
1332 uint32_t numCuInHeight = (m_param->sourceHeight + m_param->maxCUSize - 1) / m_param->maxCUSize;
1333 uint32_t widthInLowresCu = (uint32_t)m_8x8Width, heightInLowresCu = (uint32_t)m_8x8Height;
1334 double *qp_offset = 0;
1335 /* Factor in qpoffsets based on Aq/Cutree in CU costs */
1336 if (m_param->rc.aqMode || m_param->bAQMotion)
1337 qp_offset = (frames[b]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_B || !m_param->rc.cuTree) ? frames[b]->qpAqOffset : frames[b]->qpCuTreeOffset;
1338
1339 for (uint32_t row = 0; row < numCuInHeight; row++)
1340 {
1341 lowresRow = row * scale;
1342 for (uint32_t cnt = 0; cnt < scale && lowresRow < heightInLowresCu; lowresRow++, cnt++)
1343 {
1344 sum = 0; intraSum = 0;
1345 int diff = 0;
1346 lowresCuIdx = lowresRow * widthInLowresCu;
1347 for (lowresCol = 0; lowresCol < widthInLowresCu; lowresCol++, lowresCuIdx++)
1348 {
1349 uint16_t lowresCuCost = curFrame->m_lowres.lowresCostForRc[lowresCuIdx] & LOWRES_COST_MASK;
1350 if (qp_offset)
1351 {
1352 double qpOffset;
1353 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
1354 qpOffset = (qp_offset[lowresCol * 2 + lowresRow * widthInLowresCu * 4] +
1355 qp_offset[lowresCol * 2 + lowresRow * widthInLowresCu * 4 + 1] +
1356 qp_offset[lowresCol * 2 + lowresRow * widthInLowresCu * 4 + curFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRowFullRes] +
1357 qp_offset[lowresCol * 2 + lowresRow * widthInLowresCu * 4 + curFrame->m_lowres.maxBlocksInRowFullRes + 1]) / 4;
1358 else
1359 qpOffset = qp_offset[lowresCuIdx];
1360 lowresCuCost = (uint16_t)((lowresCuCost * x265_exp2fix8(qpOffset) + 128) >> 8);
1361 int32_t intraCuCost = curFrame->m_lowres.intraCost[lowresCuIdx];
1362 curFrame->m_lowres.intraCost[lowresCuIdx] = (intraCuCost * x265_exp2fix8(qpOffset) + 128) >> 8;
1363 }
1364 if (m_param->bIntraRefresh && slice->m_sliceType == X265_TYPE_P)
1365 for (uint32_t x = curFrame->m_encData->m_pir.pirStartCol; x <= curFrame->m_encData->m_pir.pirEndCol; x++)
1366 diff += curFrame->m_lowres.intraCost[lowresCuIdx] - lowresCuCost;
1367 curFrame->m_lowres.lowresCostForRc[lowresCuIdx] = lowresCuCost;
1368 sum += lowresCuCost;
1369 intraSum += curFrame->m_lowres.intraCost[lowresCuIdx];
1370 }
1371 curFrame->m_encData->m_rowStat[row].satdForVbv += sum;
1372 curFrame->m_encData->m_rowStat[row].satdForVbv += diff;
1373 curFrame->m_encData->m_rowStat[row].intraSatdForVbv += intraSum;
1374 }
1375 }
1376 }
1377 }
1378}
1379
1380void PreLookaheadGroup::processTasks(int workerThreadID)
1381{
1382 if (workerThreadID < 0)
1383 workerThreadID = m_lookahead.m_pool ? m_lookahead.m_pool->m_numWorkers : 0;
1384 LookaheadTLD& tld = m_lookahead.m_tld[workerThreadID];
1385
1386 m_lock.acquire();
1387 while (m_jobAcquired < m_jobTotal)
1388 {
1389 Frame* preFrame = m_preframes[m_jobAcquired++];
1390 ProfileLookaheadTime(m_lookahead.m_preLookaheadElapsedTime, m_lookahead.m_countPreLookahead);
1391 ProfileScopeEvent(prelookahead);
1392 m_lock.release();
1393 preFrame->m_lowres.init(preFrame->m_fencPic, preFrame->m_poc);
1394 if (m_lookahead.m_bAdaptiveQuant)
1395 tld.calcAdaptiveQuantFrame(preFrame, m_lookahead.m_param);
1396 tld.lowresIntraEstimate(preFrame->m_lowres, m_lookahead.m_param->rc.qgSize);
1397 preFrame->m_lowresInit = true;
1398
1399 m_lock.acquire();
1400 }
1401 m_lock.release();
1402}
1403
1404/* called by API thread or worker thread with inputQueueLock acquired */
1405void Lookahead::slicetypeDecide()
1406{
1407 PreLookaheadGroup pre(*this);
1408 Lowres* frames[X265_LOOKAHEAD_MAX + X265_BFRAME_MAX + 4];
1409 Frame* list[X265_BFRAME_MAX + 4];
1410 memset(frames, 0, sizeof(frames));
1411 memset(list, 0, sizeof(list));
1412 int maxSearch = X265_MIN(m_param->lookaheadDepth, X265_LOOKAHEAD_MAX);
1413 maxSearch = X265_MAX(1, maxSearch);
1414
1415 {
1416 ScopedLock lock(m_inputLock);
1417
1418 Frame *curFrame = m_inputQueue.first();
1419 int j;
1420 for (j = 0; j < m_param->bframes + 2; j++)
1421 {
1422 if (!curFrame) break;
1423 list[j] = curFrame;
1424 curFrame = curFrame->m_next;
1425 }
1426
1427 curFrame = m_inputQueue.first();
1428 frames[0] = m_lastNonB;
1429 for (j = 0; j < maxSearch; j++)
1430 {
1431 if (!curFrame) break;
1432 frames[j + 1] = &curFrame->m_lowres;
1433
1434 if (!curFrame->m_lowresInit)
1435 pre.m_preframes[pre.m_jobTotal++] = curFrame;
1436
1437 curFrame = curFrame->m_next;
1438 }
1439
1440 maxSearch = j;
1441 }
1442
1443 /* perform pre-analysis on frames which need it, using a bonded task group */
1444 if (pre.m_jobTotal)
1445 {
1446 if (m_pool)
1447 pre.tryBondPeers(*m_pool, pre.m_jobTotal);
1448 pre.processTasks(-1);
1449 pre.waitForExit();
1450 }
1451
1452 if(m_param->bEnableFades)
1453 {
1454 int j, endIndex = 0, length = X265_BFRAME_MAX + 4;
1455 for (j = 0; j < length; j++)
1456 m_frameVariance[j] = -1;
1457 for (j = 0; list[j] != NULL; j++)
1458 m_frameVariance[list[j]->m_poc % length] = list[j]->m_lowres.frameVariance;
1459 for (int k = list[0]->m_poc % length; k <= list[j - 1]->m_poc % length; k++)
1460 {
1461 if (m_frameVariance[k] == -1)
1462 break;
1463 if((k > 0 && m_frameVariance[k] >= m_frameVariance[k - 1]) ||
1464 (k == 0 && m_frameVariance[k] >= m_frameVariance[length - 1]))
1465 {
1466 m_isFadeIn = true;
1467 if (m_fadeCount == 0 && m_fadeStart == -1)
1468 {
1469 for(int temp = list[0]->m_poc; temp <= list[j - 1]->m_poc; temp++)
1470 if (k == temp % length) {
1471 m_fadeStart = temp ? temp - 1 : 0;
1472 break;
1473 }
1474 }
1475 m_fadeCount = list[endIndex]->m_poc > m_fadeStart ? list[endIndex]->m_poc - m_fadeStart : 0;
1476 endIndex++;
1477 }
1478 else
1479 {
1480 if (m_isFadeIn && m_fadeCount >= m_param->fpsNum / m_param->fpsDenom)
1481 {
1482 for (int temp = 0; list[temp] != NULL; temp++)
1483 {
1484 if (list[temp]->m_poc == m_fadeStart + (int)m_fadeCount)
1485 {
1486 list[temp]->m_lowres.bIsFadeEnd = true;
1487 break;
1488 }
1489 }
1490 }
1491 m_isFadeIn = false;
1492 m_fadeCount = 0;
1493 m_fadeStart = -1;
1494 }
1495 if (k == length - 1)
1496 k = -1;
1497 }
1498 }
1499
1500 if (m_lastNonB &&
1501 ((m_param->bFrameAdaptive && m_param->bframes) ||
1502 m_param->rc.cuTree || m_param->scenecutThreshold || m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut ||
1503 (m_param->lookaheadDepth && m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize)))
1504 {
1505 if(!m_param->rc.bStatRead)
1506 slicetypeAnalyse(frames, false);
1507 bool bIsVbv = m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize > 0 && m_param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate > 0;
1508 if ((m_param->analysisLoad && m_param->scaleFactor && bIsVbv) || m_param->bliveVBV2pass)
1509 {
1510 int numFrames;
1511 for (numFrames = 0; numFrames < maxSearch; numFrames++)
1512 {
1513 Lowres *fenc = frames[numFrames + 1];
1514 if (!fenc)
1515 break;
1516 }
1517 vbvLookahead(frames, numFrames, false);
1518 }
1519 }
1520
1521 int bframes, brefs;
1522 if (!m_param->analysisLoad || m_param->bAnalysisType == HEVC_INFO)
1523 {
1524 bool isClosedGopRadl = m_param->radl && (m_param->keyframeMax != m_param->keyframeMin);
1525 for (bframes = 0, brefs = 0;; bframes++)
1526 {
1527 Lowres& frm = list[bframes]->m_lowres;
1528
1529 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF && !m_param->bBPyramid && brefs == m_param->bBPyramid)
1530 {
1531 frm.sliceType = X265_TYPE_B;
1532 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "B-ref at frame %d incompatible with B-pyramid\n",
1533 frm.frameNum);
1534 }
1535
1536 /* pyramid with multiple B-refs needs a big enough dpb that the preceding P-frame stays available.
1537 * smaller dpb could be supported by smart enough use of mmco, but it's easier just to forbid it. */
1538 else if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF && m_param->bBPyramid && brefs &&
1539 m_param->maxNumReferences <= (brefs + 3))
1540 {
1541 frm.sliceType = X265_TYPE_B;
1542 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "B-ref at frame %d incompatible with B-pyramid and %d reference frames\n",
1543 frm.sliceType, m_param->maxNumReferences);
1544 }
1545 if (((!m_param->bIntraRefresh || frm.frameNum == 0) && frm.frameNum - m_lastKeyframe >= m_param->keyframeMax &&
1546 (!m_extendGopBoundary || frm.frameNum - m_lastKeyframe >= m_param->keyframeMax + m_param->gopLookahead)) ||
1547 (frm.frameNum == (m_param->chunkStart - 1)) || (frm.frameNum == m_param->chunkEnd))
1548 {
1549 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_AUTO || frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_I)
1550 frm.sliceType = m_param->bOpenGOP && m_lastKeyframe >= 0 ? X265_TYPE_I : X265_TYPE_IDR;
1551 bool warn = frm.sliceType != X265_TYPE_IDR;
1552 if (warn && m_param->bOpenGOP)
1553 warn &= frm.sliceType != X265_TYPE_I;
1554 if (warn)
1555 {
1556 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "specified frame type (%d) at %d is not compatible with keyframe interval\n",
1557 frm.sliceType, frm.frameNum);
1558 frm.sliceType = m_param->bOpenGOP && m_lastKeyframe >= 0 ? X265_TYPE_I : X265_TYPE_IDR;
1559 }
1560 }
1561 if (frm.bIsFadeEnd){
1562 frm.sliceType = m_param->bOpenGOP && m_lastKeyframe >= 0 ? X265_TYPE_I : X265_TYPE_IDR;
1563 }
1564 if (m_param->bResetZoneConfig)
1565 {
1566 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->rc.zonefileCount; i++)
1567 {
1568 int curZoneStart = m_param->rc.zones[i].startFrame;
1569 curZoneStart += curZoneStart ? m_param->rc.zones[i].zoneParam->radl : 0;
1570 if (curZoneStart == frm.frameNum)
1571 frm.sliceType = X265_TYPE_IDR;
1572 }
1573 }
1574 if ((frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_I && frm.frameNum - m_lastKeyframe >= m_param->keyframeMin) || (frm.frameNum == (m_param->chunkStart - 1)) || (frm.frameNum == m_param->chunkEnd))
1575 {
1576 if (m_param->bOpenGOP)
1577 {
1578 m_lastKeyframe = frm.frameNum;
1579 frm.bKeyframe = true;
1580 }
1581 else
1582 frm.sliceType = X265_TYPE_IDR;
1583 }
1584 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR && frm.bScenecut && isClosedGopRadl)
1585 {
1586 if (!m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut || (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && frm.m_bIsHardScenecut))
1587 {
1588 for (int i = bframes; i < bframes + m_param->radl; i++)
1589 list[i]->m_lowres.sliceType = X265_TYPE_B;
1590 list[(bframes + m_param->radl)]->m_lowres.sliceType = X265_TYPE_IDR;
1591 }
1592 }
1593 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR)
1594 {
1595 /* Closed GOP */
1596 m_lastKeyframe = frm.frameNum;
1597 frm.bKeyframe = true;
1598 int zoneRadl = 0;
1599 if (m_param->bResetZoneConfig)
1600 {
1601 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->rc.zonefileCount; i++)
1602 {
1603 int zoneStart = m_param->rc.zones[i].startFrame;
1604 zoneStart += zoneStart ? m_param->rc.zones[i].zoneParam->radl : 0;
1605 if (zoneStart == frm.frameNum)
1606 {
1607 zoneRadl = m_param->rc.zones[i].zoneParam->radl;
1608 m_param->radl = 0;
1609 m_param->rc.zones->zoneParam->radl = i < m_param->rc.zonefileCount - 1 ? m_param->rc.zones[i + 1].zoneParam->radl : 0;
1610 break;
1611 }
1612 }
1613 }
1614 if (bframes > 0 && !m_param->radl && !zoneRadl)
1615 {
1616 list[bframes - 1]->m_lowres.sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
1617 bframes--;
1618 }
1619 }
1620 if (bframes == m_param->bframes || !list[bframes + 1])
1621 {
1622 if (IS_X265_TYPE_B(frm.sliceType))
1623 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_WARNING, "specified frame type is not compatible with max B-frames\n");
1624 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_AUTO || IS_X265_TYPE_B(frm.sliceType))
1625 frm.sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
1626 }
1627 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF)
1628 brefs++;
1629 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_AUTO)
1630 frm.sliceType = X265_TYPE_B;
1631 else if (!IS_X265_TYPE_B(frm.sliceType))
1632 break;
1633 }
1634 }
1635 else
1636 {
1637 for (bframes = 0, brefs = 0;; bframes++)
1638 {
1639 Lowres& frm = list[bframes]->m_lowres;
1640 if (frm.sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF)
1641 brefs++;
1642 if ((IS_X265_TYPE_I(frm.sliceType) && frm.frameNum - m_lastKeyframe >= m_param->keyframeMin)
1643 || (frm.frameNum == (m_param->chunkStart - 1)) || (frm.frameNum == m_param->chunkEnd))
1644 {
1645 m_lastKeyframe = frm.frameNum;
1646 frm.bKeyframe = true;
1647 }
1648 if (!IS_X265_TYPE_B(frm.sliceType))
1649 break;
1650 }
1651 }
1652 if (bframes)
1653 list[bframes - 1]->m_lowres.bLastMiniGopBFrame = true;
1654 list[bframes]->m_lowres.leadingBframes = bframes;
1655 m_lastNonB = &list[bframes]->m_lowres;
1656 m_histogram[bframes]++;
1657
1658 /* insert a bref into the sequence */
1659 if (m_param->bBPyramid && bframes > 1 && !brefs)
1660 {
1661 list[bframes / 2]->m_lowres.sliceType = X265_TYPE_BREF;
1662 brefs++;
1663 }
1664 /* calculate the frame costs ahead of time for estimateFrameCost while we still have lowres */
1665 if (m_param->rc.rateControlMode != X265_RC_CQP)
1666 {
1667 int p0, p1, b;
1668 /* For zero latency tuning, calculate frame cost to be used later in RC */
1669 if (!maxSearch)
1670 {
1671 for (int i = 0; i <= bframes; i++)
1672 frames[i + 1] = &list[i]->m_lowres;
1673 }
1674
1675 /* estimate new non-B cost */
1676 p1 = b = bframes + 1;
1677 p0 = (IS_X265_TYPE_I(frames[bframes + 1]->sliceType)) ? b : 0;
1678
1679 CostEstimateGroup estGroup(*this, frames);
1680
1681 estGroup.singleCost(p0, p1, b);
1682
1683 if (bframes)
1684 {
1685 p0 = 0; // last nonb
1686 bool isp0available = frames[bframes + 1]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_IDR ? false : true;
1687
1688 for (b = 1; b <= bframes; b++)
1689 {
1690 if (!isp0available)
1691 p0 = b;
1692
1693 if (frames[b]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_B)
1694 for (p1 = b; frames[p1]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_B; p1++)
1695 ; // find new nonb or bref
1696 else
1697 p1 = bframes + 1;
1698
1699 estGroup.singleCost(p0, p1, b);
1700
1701 if (frames[b]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF)
1702 {
1703 p0 = b;
1704 isp0available = true;
1705 }
1706 }
1707 }
1708 }
1709
1710 m_inputLock.acquire();
1711 /* dequeue all frames from inputQueue that are about to be enqueued
1712 * in the output queue. The order is important because Frame can
1713 * only be in one list at a time */
1714 int64_t pts[X265_BFRAME_MAX + 1];
1715 for (int i = 0; i <= bframes; i++)
1716 {
1717 Frame *curFrame;
1718 curFrame = m_inputQueue.popFront();
1719 pts[i] = curFrame->m_pts;
1720 maxSearch--;
1721 }
1722 m_inputLock.release();
1723
1724 m_outputLock.acquire();
1725 /* add non-B to output queue */
1726 int idx = 0;
1727 list[bframes]->m_reorderedPts = pts[idx++];
1728 m_outputQueue.pushBack(*list[bframes]);
1729 /* Add B-ref frame next to P frame in output queue, the B-ref encode before non B-ref frame */
1730 if (brefs)
1731 {
1732 for (int i = 0; i < bframes; i++)
1733 {
1734 if (list[i]->m_lowres.sliceType == X265_TYPE_BREF)
1735 {
1736 list[i]->m_reorderedPts = pts[idx++];
1737 m_outputQueue.pushBack(*list[i]);
1738 }
1739 }
1740 }
1741
1742 /* add B frames to output queue */
1743 for (int i = 0; i < bframes; i++)
1744 {
1745 /* push all the B frames into output queue except B-ref, which already pushed into output queue */
1746 if (list[i]->m_lowres.sliceType != X265_TYPE_BREF)
1747 {
1748 list[i]->m_reorderedPts = pts[idx++];
1749 m_outputQueue.pushBack(*list[i]);
1750 }
1751 }
1752
1753 bool isKeyFrameAnalyse = (m_param->rc.cuTree || (m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize && m_param->lookaheadDepth));
1754 if (isKeyFrameAnalyse && IS_X265_TYPE_I(m_lastNonB->sliceType))
1755 {
1756 m_inputLock.acquire();
1757 Frame *curFrame = m_inputQueue.first();
1758 frames[0] = m_lastNonB;
1759 int j;
1760 for (j = 0; j < maxSearch; j++)
1761 {
1762 frames[j + 1] = &curFrame->m_lowres;
1763 curFrame = curFrame->m_next;
1764 }
1765 m_inputLock.release();
1766
1767 frames[j + 1] = NULL;
1768 if (!m_param->rc.bStatRead)
1769 slicetypeAnalyse(frames, true);
1770 bool bIsVbv = m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize > 0 && m_param->rc.vbvMaxBitrate > 0;
1771 if ((m_param->analysisLoad && m_param->scaleFactor && bIsVbv) || m_param->bliveVBV2pass)
1772 {
1773 int numFrames;
1774 for (numFrames = 0; numFrames < maxSearch; numFrames++)
1775 {
1776 Lowres *fenc = frames[numFrames + 1];
1777 if (!fenc)
1778 break;
1779 }
1780 vbvLookahead(frames, numFrames, true);
1781 }
1782 }
1783 m_outputLock.release();
1784}
1785
1786void Lookahead::vbvLookahead(Lowres **frames, int numFrames, int keyframe)
1787{
1788 int prevNonB = 0, curNonB = 1, idx = 0;
1789 while (curNonB < numFrames && IS_X265_TYPE_B(frames[curNonB]->sliceType))
1790 curNonB++;
1791 int nextNonB = keyframe ? prevNonB : curNonB;
1792 int nextB = prevNonB + 1;
1793 int nextBRef = 0, curBRef = 0;
1794 if (m_param->bBPyramid && curNonB - prevNonB > 1)
1795 curBRef = (prevNonB + curNonB + 1) / 2;
1796 int miniGopEnd = keyframe ? prevNonB : curNonB;
1797 while (curNonB <= numFrames)
1798 {
1799 /* P/I cost: This shouldn't include the cost of nextNonB */
1800 if (nextNonB != curNonB)
1801 {
1802 int p0 = IS_X265_TYPE_I(frames[curNonB]->sliceType) ? curNonB : prevNonB;
1803 frames[nextNonB]->plannedSatd[idx] = vbvFrameCost(frames, p0, curNonB, curNonB);
1804 frames[nextNonB]->plannedType[idx] = frames[curNonB]->sliceType;
1805
1806 /* Save the nextNonB Cost in each B frame of the current miniGop */
1807 if (curNonB > miniGopEnd)
1808 {
1809 for (int j = nextB; j < miniGopEnd; j++)
1810 {
1811 frames[j]->plannedSatd[frames[j]->indB] = frames[nextNonB]->plannedSatd[idx];
1812 frames[j]->plannedType[frames[j]->indB++] = frames[nextNonB]->plannedType[idx];
1813 }
1814 }
1815 idx++;
1816 }
1817
1818 /* Handle the B-frames: coded order */
1819 if (m_param->bBPyramid && curNonB - prevNonB > 1)
1820 nextBRef = (prevNonB + curNonB + 1) / 2;
1821
1822 for (int i = prevNonB + 1; i < curNonB; i++, idx++)
1823 {
1824 int64_t satdCost = 0;
1825 int type = X265_TYPE_B;
1826 if (nextBRef)
1827 {
1828 if (i == nextBRef)
1829 {
1830 satdCost = vbvFrameCost(frames, prevNonB, curNonB, nextBRef);
1831 type = X265_TYPE_BREF;
1832 }
1833 else if (i < nextBRef)
1834 satdCost = vbvFrameCost(frames, prevNonB, nextBRef, i);
1835 else
1836 satdCost = vbvFrameCost(frames, nextBRef, curNonB, i);
1837 }
1838 else
1839 satdCost = vbvFrameCost(frames, prevNonB, curNonB, i);
1840 frames[nextNonB]->plannedSatd[idx] = satdCost;
1841 frames[nextNonB]->plannedType[idx] = type;
1842 /* Save the nextB Cost in each B frame of the current miniGop */
1843
1844 for (int j = nextB; j < miniGopEnd; j++)
1845 {
1846 if (curBRef && curBRef == i)
1847 break;
1848 if (j >= i && j !=nextBRef)
1849 continue;
1850 frames[j]->plannedSatd[frames[j]->indB] = satdCost;
1851 frames[j]->plannedType[frames[j]->indB++] = type;
1852 }
1853 }
1854 prevNonB = curNonB;
1855 curNonB++;
1856 while (curNonB <= numFrames && IS_X265_TYPE_B(frames[curNonB]->sliceType))
1857 curNonB++;
1858 }
1859
1860 frames[nextNonB]->plannedType[idx] = X265_TYPE_AUTO;
1861}
1862
1863int64_t Lookahead::vbvFrameCost(Lowres **frames, int p0, int p1, int b)
1864{
1865 CostEstimateGroup estGroup(*this, frames);
1866 int64_t cost = estGroup.singleCost(p0, p1, b);
1867
1868 if (m_param->rc.aqMode || m_param->bAQMotion)
1869 {
1870 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
1871 return frameCostRecalculate(frames, p0, p1, b);
1872 else
1873 return frames[b]->costEstAq[b - p0][p1 - b];
1874 }
1875
1876 return cost;
1877}
1878
1879void Lookahead::slicetypeAnalyse(Lowres **frames, bool bKeyframe)
1880{
1881 int numFrames, origNumFrames, keyintLimit, framecnt;
1882 int maxSearch = X265_MIN(m_param->lookaheadDepth, X265_LOOKAHEAD_MAX);
1883 int cuCount = m_8x8Blocks;
1884 int resetStart;
1885 bool bIsVbvLookahead = m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize && m_param->lookaheadDepth;
1886
1887 /* count undecided frames */
1888 for (framecnt = 0; framecnt < maxSearch; framecnt++)
1889 {
1890 Lowres *fenc = frames[framecnt + 1];
1891 if (!fenc || fenc->sliceType != X265_TYPE_AUTO)
1892 break;
1893 }
1894
1895 if (!framecnt)
1896 {
1897 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
1898 cuTree(frames, 0, bKeyframe);
1899 return;
1900 }
1901 frames[framecnt + 1] = NULL;
1902
1903 if (m_param->bResetZoneConfig)
1904 {
1905 for (int i = 0; i < m_param->rc.zonefileCount; i++)
1906 {
1907 int curZoneStart = m_param->rc.zones[i].startFrame, nextZoneStart = 0;
1908 curZoneStart += curZoneStart ? m_param->rc.zones[i].zoneParam->radl : 0;
1909 nextZoneStart += (i + 1 < m_param->rc.zonefileCount) ? m_param->rc.zones[i + 1].startFrame + m_param->rc.zones[i + 1].zoneParam->radl : m_param->totalFrames;
1910 if (curZoneStart <= frames[0]->frameNum && nextZoneStart > frames[0]->frameNum)
1911 m_param->keyframeMax = nextZoneStart - curZoneStart;
1912 }
1913 }
1914 int keylimit = m_param->keyframeMax;
1915 if (frames[0]->frameNum < m_param->chunkEnd)
1916 {
1917 int chunkStart = (m_param->chunkStart - m_lastKeyframe - 1);
1918 int chunkEnd = (m_param->chunkEnd - m_lastKeyframe);
1919 if ((chunkStart > 0) && (chunkStart < m_param->keyframeMax))
1920 keylimit = chunkStart;
1921 else if ((chunkEnd > 0) && (chunkEnd < m_param->keyframeMax))
1922 keylimit = chunkEnd;
1923 }
1924
1925 int keyFrameLimit = keylimit + m_lastKeyframe - frames[0]->frameNum - 1;
1926 if (m_param->gopLookahead && keyFrameLimit <= m_param->bframes + 1)
1927 keyintLimit = keyFrameLimit + m_param->gopLookahead;
1928 else
1929 keyintLimit = keyFrameLimit;
1930
1931 origNumFrames = numFrames = m_param->bIntraRefresh ? framecnt : X265_MIN(framecnt, keyintLimit);
1932 if (bIsVbvLookahead)
1933 numFrames = framecnt;
1934 else if (m_param->bOpenGOP && numFrames < framecnt)
1935 numFrames++;
1936 else if (numFrames == 0)
1937 {
1938 frames[1]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_I;
1939 return;
1940 }
1941
1942 if (m_bBatchMotionSearch)
1943 {
1944 /* pre-calculate all motion searches, using many worker threads */
1945 CostEstimateGroup estGroup(*this, frames);
1946 for (int b = 2; b < numFrames; b++)
1947 {
1948 for (int i = 1; i <= m_param->bframes + 1; i++)
1949 {
1950 int p0 = b - i;
1951 if (p0 < 0)
1952 continue;
1953
1954 /* Skip search if already done */
1955 if (frames[b]->lowresMvs[0][i][0].x != 0x7FFF)
1956 continue;
1957
1958 /* perform search to p1 at same distance, if possible */
1959 int p1 = b + i;
1960 if (p1 >= numFrames || frames[b]->lowresMvs[1][i][0].x != 0x7FFF)
1961 p1 = b;
1962
1963 estGroup.add(p0, p1, b);
1964 }
1965 }
1966 /* auto-disable after the first batch if pool is small */
1967 m_bBatchMotionSearch &= m_pool->m_numWorkers >= 4;
1968 estGroup.finishBatch();
1969
1970 if (m_bBatchFrameCosts)
1971 {
1972 /* pre-calculate all frame cost estimates, using many worker threads */
1973 for (int b = 2; b < numFrames; b++)
1974 {
1975 for (int i = 1; i <= m_param->bframes + 1; i++)
1976 {
1977 if (b < i)
1978 continue;
1979
1980 /* only measure frame cost in this pass if motion searches
1981 * are already done */
1982 if (frames[b]->lowresMvs[0][i][0].x == 0x7FFF)
1983 continue;
1984
1985 int p0 = b - i;
1986
1987 for (int j = 0; j <= m_param->bframes; j++)
1988 {
1989 int p1 = b + j;
1990 if (p1 >= numFrames)
1991 break;
1992
1993 /* ensure P1 search is done */
1994 if (j && frames[b]->lowresMvs[1][j][0].x == 0x7FFF)
1995 continue;
1996
1997 /* ensure frame cost is not done */
1998 if (frames[b]->costEst[i][j] >= 0)
1999 continue;
2000
2001 estGroup.add(p0, p1, b);
2002 }
2003 }
2004 }
2005
2006 /* auto-disable after the first batch if the pool is not large */
2007 m_bBatchFrameCosts &= m_pool->m_numWorkers > 12;
2008 estGroup.finishBatch();
2009 }
2010 }
2011
2012 int numBFrames = 0;
2013 int numAnalyzed = numFrames;
2014 bool isScenecut = false;
2015
2016 /* Temporal computations for scenecut detection */
2017 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
2018 {
2019 for (int i = numFrames - 1; i > 0; i--)
2020 {
2021 if (frames[i]->interPCostPercDiff > 0.0)
2022 continue;
2023 int64_t interCost = frames[i]->costEst[1][0];
2024 int64_t intraCost = frames[i]->costEst[0][0];
2025 if (interCost < 0 || intraCost < 0)
2026 continue;
2027 int times = 0;
2028 double averagePcost = 0.0, averageIcost = 0.0;
2029 for (int j = i - 1; j >= 0 && times < 5; j--, times++)
2030 {
2031 if (frames[j]->costEst[0][0] > 0 && frames[j]->costEst[1][0] > 0)
2032 {
2033 averageIcost += frames[j]->costEst[0][0];
2034 averagePcost += frames[j]->costEst[1][0];
2035 }
2036 else
2037 times--;
2038 }
2039 if (times)
2040 {
2041 averageIcost = averageIcost / times;
2042 averagePcost = averagePcost / times;
2043 frames[i]->interPCostPercDiff = abs(interCost - averagePcost) / X265_MIN(interCost, averagePcost) * 100;
2044 frames[i]->intraCostPercDiff = abs(intraCost - averageIcost) / X265_MIN(intraCost, averageIcost) * 100;
2045 }
2046 }
2047 }
2048
2049 /* When scenecut threshold is set, use scenecut detection for I frame placements */
2050 if (!m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut || (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && frames[1]->bScenecut))
2051 isScenecut = scenecut(frames, 0, 1, true, origNumFrames);
2052
2053 if (isScenecut && (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut || m_param->scenecutThreshold))
2054 {
2055 frames[1]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_I;
2056 return;
2057 }
2058 if (m_param->gopLookahead && (keyFrameLimit >= 0) && (keyFrameLimit <= m_param->bframes + 1))
2059 {
2060 bool sceneTransition = m_isSceneTransition;
2061 m_extendGopBoundary = false;
2062 for (int i = m_param->bframes + 1; i < origNumFrames; i += m_param->bframes + 1)
2063 {
2064 if (!m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut || (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && frames[i + 1]->bScenecut))
2065 scenecut(frames, i, i + 1, true, origNumFrames);
2066
2067 for (int j = i + 1; j <= X265_MIN(i + m_param->bframes + 1, origNumFrames); j++)
2068 {
2069 if (frames[j]->bScenecut && scenecutInternal(frames, j - 1, j, true))
2070 {
2071 m_extendGopBoundary = true;
2072 break;
2073 }
2074 }
2075 if (m_extendGopBoundary)
2076 break;
2077 }
2078 m_isSceneTransition = sceneTransition;
2079 }
2080 if (m_param->bframes)
2081 {
2082 if (m_param->bFrameAdaptive == X265_B_ADAPT_TRELLIS)
2083 {
2084 if (numFrames > 1)
2085 {
2086 char best_paths[X265_BFRAME_MAX + 1][X265_LOOKAHEAD_MAX + 1] = { "", "P" };
2087 int best_path_index = numFrames % (X265_BFRAME_MAX + 1);
2088
2089 /* Perform the frame type analysis. */
2090 for (int j = 2; j <= numFrames; j++)
2091 slicetypePath(frames, j, best_paths);
2092
2093 numBFrames = (int)strspn(best_paths[best_path_index], "B");
2094
2095 /* Load the results of the analysis into the frame types. */
2096 for (int j = 1; j < numFrames; j++)
2097 frames[j]->sliceType = best_paths[best_path_index][j - 1] == 'B' ? X265_TYPE_B : X265_TYPE_P;
2098 }
2099 frames[numFrames]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2100 }
2101 else if (m_param->bFrameAdaptive == X265_B_ADAPT_FAST)
2102 {
2103 CostEstimateGroup estGroup(*this, frames);
2104
2105 int64_t cost1p0, cost2p0, cost1b1, cost2p1;
2106
2107 for (int i = 0; i <= numFrames - 2; )
2108 {
2109 cost2p1 = estGroup.singleCost(i + 0, i + 2, i + 2, true);
2110 if (frames[i + 2]->intraMbs[2] > cuCount / 2)
2111 {
2112 frames[i + 1]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2113 frames[i + 2]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2114 i += 2;
2115 continue;
2116 }
2117
2118 cost1b1 = estGroup.singleCost(i + 0, i + 2, i + 1);
2119 cost1p0 = estGroup.singleCost(i + 0, i + 1, i + 1);
2120 cost2p0 = estGroup.singleCost(i + 1, i + 2, i + 2);
2121
2122 if (cost1p0 + cost2p0 < cost1b1 + cost2p1)
2123 {
2124 frames[i + 1]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2125 i += 1;
2126 continue;
2127 }
2128
2129// arbitrary and untuned
2130#define INTER_THRESH 300
2131#define P_SENS_BIAS (50 - m_param->bFrameBias)
2132 frames[i + 1]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_B;
2133
2134 int j;
2135 for (j = i + 2; j <= X265_MIN(i + m_param->bframes, numFrames - 1); j++)
2136 {
2137 int64_t pthresh = X265_MAX(INTER_THRESH - P_SENS_BIAS * (j - i - 1), INTER_THRESH / 10);
2138 int64_t pcost = estGroup.singleCost(i + 0, j + 1, j + 1, true);
2139 if (pcost > pthresh * cuCount || frames[j + 1]->intraMbs[j - i + 1] > cuCount / 3)
2140 break;
2141 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_B;
2142 }
2143
2144 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2145 i = j;
2146 }
2147 frames[numFrames]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2148 numBFrames = 0;
2149 while (numBFrames < numFrames && frames[numBFrames + 1]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_B)
2150 numBFrames++;
2151 }
2152 else
2153 {
2154 numBFrames = X265_MIN(numFrames - 1, m_param->bframes);
2155 for (int j = 1; j < numFrames; j++)
2156 frames[j]->sliceType = (j % (numBFrames + 1)) ? X265_TYPE_B : X265_TYPE_P;
2157
2158 frames[numFrames]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2159 }
2160
2161 int zoneRadl = m_param->rc.zonefileCount && m_param->bResetZoneConfig ? m_param->rc.zones->zoneParam->radl : 0;
2162 bool bForceRADL = zoneRadl || (m_param->radl && (m_param->keyframeMax == m_param->keyframeMin));
2163 bool bLastMiniGop = (framecnt >= m_param->bframes + 1) ? false : true;
2164 int radl = m_param->radl ? m_param->radl : zoneRadl;
2165 int preRADL = m_lastKeyframe + m_param->keyframeMax - radl - 1; /*Frame preceeding RADL in POC order*/
2166 if (bForceRADL && (frames[0]->frameNum == preRADL) && !bLastMiniGop)
2167 {
2168 int j = 1;
2169 numBFrames = m_param->radl ? m_param->radl : zoneRadl;
2170 for (; j <= numBFrames; j++)
2171 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_B;
2172 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_I;
2173 }
2174 else /* Check scenecut and RADL on the first minigop. */
2175 {
2176 for (int j = 1; j < numBFrames + 1; j++)
2177 {
2178 bool isNextScenecut = false;
2179 if (!m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut || (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && frames[j + 1]->bScenecut))
2180 isNextScenecut = scenecut(frames, j, j + 1, false, origNumFrames);
2181 if (isNextScenecut || (bForceRADL && frames[j]->frameNum == preRADL))
2182 {
2183 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2184 numAnalyzed = j;
2185 break;
2186 }
2187 }
2188 }
2189 resetStart = bKeyframe ? 1 : X265_MIN(numBFrames + 2, numAnalyzed + 1);
2190 }
2191 else
2192 {
2193 for (int j = 1; j <= numFrames; j++)
2194 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_P;
2195
2196 resetStart = bKeyframe ? 1 : 2;
2197 }
2198 if (m_param->bAQMotion)
2199 aqMotion(frames, bKeyframe);
2200
2201 if (m_param->rc.cuTree)
2202 cuTree(frames, X265_MIN(numFrames, m_param->keyframeMax), bKeyframe);
2203
2204 if (m_param->gopLookahead && (keyFrameLimit >= 0) && (keyFrameLimit <= m_param->bframes + 1) && !m_extendGopBoundary)
2205 keyintLimit = keyFrameLimit;
2206
2207 if (!m_param->bIntraRefresh)
2208 for (int j = keyintLimit + 1; j <= numFrames; j += m_param->keyframeMax)
2209 {
2210 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_I;
2211 resetStart = X265_MIN(resetStart, j + 1);
2212 }
2213
2214 if (bIsVbvLookahead)
2215 vbvLookahead(frames, numFrames, bKeyframe);
2216 int maxp1 = X265_MIN(m_param->bframes + 1, origNumFrames);
2217
2218 /* Restore frame types for all frames that haven't actually been decided yet. */
2219 for (int j = resetStart; j <= numFrames; j++)
2220 {
2221 frames[j]->sliceType = X265_TYPE_AUTO;
2222 /* If any frame marked as scenecut is being restarted for sliceDecision,
2223 * undo scene Transition flag */
2224 if (j <= maxp1 && frames[j]->bScenecut && m_isSceneTransition)
2225 m_isSceneTransition = false;
2226 }
2227}
2228
2229bool Lookahead::scenecut(Lowres **frames, int p0, int p1, bool bRealScenecut, int numFrames)
2230{
2231 /* Only do analysis during a normal scenecut check. */
2232 if (bRealScenecut && m_param->bframes)
2233 {
2234 int origmaxp1 = p0 + 1;
2235 /* Look ahead to avoid coding short flashes as scenecuts. */
2236 origmaxp1 += m_param->bframes;
2237 int maxp1 = X265_MIN(origmaxp1, numFrames);
2238 bool fluctuate = false;
2239 bool noScenecuts = false;
2240 int64_t avgSatdCost = 0;
2241 if (frames[p0]->costEst[p1 - p0][0] > -1)
2242 avgSatdCost = frames[p0]->costEst[p1 - p0][0];
2243 int cnt = 1;
2244 /* Where A and B are scenes: AAAAAABBBAAAAAA
2245 * If BBB is shorter than (maxp1-p0), it is detected as a flash
2246 * and not considered a scenecut. */
2247 for (int cp1 = p1; cp1 <= maxp1; cp1++)
2248 {
2249 if (!scenecutInternal(frames, p0, cp1, false) && !m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
2250 {
2251 /* Any frame in between p0 and cur_p1 cannot be a real scenecut. */
2252 for (int i = cp1; i > p0; i--)
2253 {
2254 frames[i]->bScenecut = false;
2255 noScenecuts = false;
2256 }
2257 }
2258 else if ((m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && frames[cp1]->m_bIsMaxThres) || scenecutInternal(frames, cp1 - 1, cp1, false))
2259 {
2260 /* If current frame is a Scenecut from p0 frame as well as Scenecut from
2261 * preceeding frame, mark it as a Scenecut */
2262 frames[cp1]->bScenecut = true;
2263 noScenecuts = true;
2264 }
2265
2266 /* compute average satdcost of all the frames in the mini-gop to confirm
2267 * whether there is any great fluctuation among them to rule out false positives */
2268 X265_CHECK(frames[cp1]->costEst[cp1 - p0][0]!= -1, "costEst is not done \n");
2269 avgSatdCost += frames[cp1]->costEst[cp1 - p0][0];
2270 cnt++;
2271 }
2272
2273 /* Identify possible scene fluctuations by comparing the satd cost of the frames.
2274 * This could denote the beginning or ending of scene transitions.
2275 * During a scene transition(fade in/fade outs), if fluctuate remains false,
2276 * then the scene had completed its transition or stabilized */
2277 if (noScenecuts)
2278 {
2279 fluctuate = false;
2280 avgSatdCost /= cnt;
2281 for (int i = p1; i <= maxp1; i++)
2282 {
2283 int64_t curCost = frames[i]->costEst[i - p0][0];
2284 int64_t prevCost = frames[i - 1]->costEst[i - 1 - p0][0];
2285 if (fabs((double)(curCost - avgSatdCost)) > 0.1 * avgSatdCost ||
2286 fabs((double)(curCost - prevCost)) > 0.1 * prevCost)
2287 {
2288 fluctuate = true;
2289 if (!m_isSceneTransition && frames[i]->bScenecut)
2290 {
2291 m_isSceneTransition = true;
2292 /* just mark the first scenechange in the scene transition as a scenecut. */
2293 for (int j = i + 1; j <= maxp1; j++)
2294 frames[j]->bScenecut = false;
2295 break;
2296 }
2297 }
2298 frames[i]->bScenecut = false;
2299 }
2300 }
2301 if (!fluctuate && !noScenecuts)
2302 m_isSceneTransition = false; /* Signal end of scene transitioning */
2303 }
2304
2305 if (m_param->csvLogLevel >= 2)
2306 {
2307 int64_t icost = frames[p1]->costEst[0][0];
2308 int64_t pcost = frames[p1]->costEst[p1 - p0][0];
2309 frames[p1]->ipCostRatio = (double)icost / pcost;
2310 }
2311
2312 /* A frame is always analysed with bRealScenecut = true first, and then bRealScenecut = false,
2313 the former for I decisions and the latter for P/B decisions. It's possible that the first
2314 analysis detected scenecuts which were later nulled due to scene transitioning, in which
2315 case do not return a true scenecut for this frame */
2316
2317 if (!frames[p1]->bScenecut)
2318 return false;
2319 /* Check only scene transitions if max threshold */
2320 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut && frames[p1]->m_bIsMaxThres)
2321 return frames[p1]->bScenecut;
2322
2323 return scenecutInternal(frames, p0, p1, bRealScenecut);
2324}
2325
2326bool Lookahead::scenecutInternal(Lowres **frames, int p0, int p1, bool bRealScenecut)
2327{
2328 Lowres *frame = frames[p1];
2329
2330 CostEstimateGroup estGroup(*this, frames);
