2331 estGroup.singleCost(p0, p1, p1);
2332 int64_t icost = frame->costEst[0][0];
2333 int64_t pcost = frame->costEst[p1 - p0][0];
2334 int gopSize = (frame->frameNum - m_lastKeyframe) % m_param->keyframeMax;
2335 float threshMax = (float)(m_param->scenecutThreshold / 100.0);
2336 /* magic numbers pulled out of thin air */
2337 float threshMin = (float)(threshMax * 0.25);
2338 double bias = m_param->scenecutBias;
2339 if (m_param->bHistBasedSceneCut)
2340 {
2341 double minT = TEMPORAL_SCENECUT_THRESHOLD * (1 + m_param->edgeTransitionThreshold);
2342 if (frame->interPCostPercDiff > minT || frame->intraCostPercDiff > minT)
2343 {
2344 if (bRealScenecut && frame->bScenecut)
2345 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_DEBUG, "scene cut at %d \n", frame->frameNum);
2346 return frame->bScenecut;
2347 }
2348 else
2349 return false;
2350 }
2351 else if (bRealScenecut)
2352 {
2353 if (m_param->keyframeMin == m_param->keyframeMax)
2354 threshMin = threshMax;
2355 if (gopSize <= m_param->keyframeMin / 4 || m_param->bIntraRefresh)
2356 bias = threshMin / 4;
2357 else if (gopSize <= m_param->keyframeMin)
2358 bias = threshMin * gopSize / m_param->keyframeMin;
2359 else
2360 {
2361 bias = threshMin
2362 + (threshMax - threshMin)
2363 * (gopSize - m_param->keyframeMin)
2364 / (m_param->keyframeMax - m_param->keyframeMin);
2365 }
2366 }
2367 bool res = pcost >= (1.0 - bias) * icost;
2368 if (res && bRealScenecut)
2369 {
2370 int imb = frame->intraMbs[p1 - p0];
2371 int pmb = m_8x8Blocks - imb;
2372 x265_log(m_param, X265_LOG_DEBUG, "scene cut at %d Icost:%d Pcost:%d ratio:%.4f bias:%.4f gop:%d (imb:%d pmb:%d)\n",
2373 frame->frameNum, icost, pcost, 1. - (double)pcost / icost, bias, gopSize, imb, pmb);
2374 }
2375 return res;
2376}
2377
2378void Lookahead::slicetypePath(Lowres **frames, int length, char(*best_paths)[X265_LOOKAHEAD_MAX + 1])
2379{
2380 char paths[2][X265_LOOKAHEAD_MAX + 1];
2381 int num_paths = X265_MIN(m_param->bframes + 1, length);
2382 int64_t best_cost = 1LL << 62;
2383 int idx = 0;
2384
2385 /* Iterate over all currently possible paths */
2386 for (int path = 0; path < num_paths; path++)
2387 {
2388 /* Add suffixes to the current path */
2389 int len = length - (path + 1);
2390 memcpy(paths[idx], best_paths[len % (X265_BFRAME_MAX + 1)], len);
2391 memset(paths[idx] + len, 'B', path);
2392 strcpy(paths[idx] + len + path, "P");
2393
2394 /* Calculate the actual cost of the current path */
2395 int64_t cost = slicetypePathCost(frames, paths[idx], best_cost);
2396 if (cost < best_cost)
2397 {
2398 best_cost = cost;
2399 idx ^= 1;
2400 }
2401 }
2402
2403 /* Store the best path. */
2404 memcpy(best_paths[length % (X265_BFRAME_MAX + 1)], paths[idx ^ 1], length);
2405}
2406
2407int64_t Lookahead::slicetypePathCost(Lowres **frames, char *path, int64_t threshold)
2408{
2409 int64_t cost = 0;
2410 int loc = 1;
2411 int cur_p = 0;
2412
2413 CostEstimateGroup estGroup(*this, frames);
2414
2415 path--; /* Since the 1st path element is really the second frame */
2416 while (path[loc])
2417 {
2418 int next_p = loc;
2419 /* Find the location of the next P-frame. */
2420 while (path[next_p] != 'P')
2421 next_p++;
2422
2423 /* Add the cost of the P-frame found above */
2424 cost += estGroup.singleCost(cur_p, next_p, next_p);
2425
2426 /* Early terminate if the cost we have found is larger than the best path cost so far */
2427 if (cost > threshold)
2428 break;
2429
2430 if (m_param->bBPyramid && next_p - cur_p > 2)
2431 {
2432 int middle = cur_p + (next_p - cur_p) / 2;
2433 cost += estGroup.singleCost(cur_p, next_p, middle);
2434
2435 for (int next_b = loc; next_b < middle && cost < threshold; next_b++)
2436 cost += estGroup.singleCost(cur_p, middle, next_b);
2437
2438 for (int next_b = middle + 1; next_b < next_p && cost < threshold; next_b++)
2439 cost += estGroup.singleCost(middle, next_p, next_b);
2440 }
2441 else
2442 {
2443 for (int next_b = loc; next_b < next_p && cost < threshold; next_b++)
2444 cost += estGroup.singleCost(cur_p, next_p, next_b);
2445 }
2446
2447 loc = next_p + 1;
2448 cur_p = next_p;
2449 }
2450
2451 return cost;
2452}
2453
2454void Lookahead::aqMotion(Lowres **frames, bool bIntra)
2455{
2456 if (!bIntra)
2457 {
2458 int curnonb = 0, lastnonb = 1;
2459 int bframes = 0, i = 1;
2460 while (frames[lastnonb]->sliceType != X265_TYPE_P)
2461 lastnonb++;
2462 bframes = lastnonb - 1;
2463 if (m_param->bBPyramid && bframes > 1)
2464 {
2465 int middle = (bframes + 1) / 2;
2466 for (i = 1; i < lastnonb; i++)
2467 {
2468 int p0 = i > middle ? middle : curnonb;
2469 int p1 = i < middle ? middle : lastnonb;
2470 if (i != middle)
2471 calcMotionAdaptiveQuantFrame(frames, p0, p1, i);
2472 }
2473 calcMotionAdaptiveQuantFrame(frames, curnonb, lastnonb, middle);
2474 }
2475 else
2476 for (i = 1; i < lastnonb; i++)
2477 calcMotionAdaptiveQuantFrame(frames, curnonb, lastnonb, i);
2478 calcMotionAdaptiveQuantFrame(frames, curnonb, lastnonb, lastnonb);
2479 }
2480}
2481
2482void Lookahead::calcMotionAdaptiveQuantFrame(Lowres **frames, int p0, int p1, int b)
2483{
2484 int listDist[2] = { b - p0, p1 - b };
2485 int32_t strideInCU = m_8x8Width;
2486 double qp_adj = 0, avg_adj = 0, avg_adj_pow2 = 0, sd;
2487 for (uint16_t blocky = 0; blocky < m_8x8Height; blocky++)
2488 {
2489 int cuIndex = blocky * strideInCU;
2490 for (uint16_t blockx = 0; blockx < m_8x8Width; blockx++, cuIndex++)
2491 {
2492 int32_t lists_used = frames[b]->lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b][cuIndex] >> LOWRES_COST_SHIFT;
2493 double displacement = 0;
2494 for (uint16_t list = 0; list < 2; list++)
2495 {
2496 if ((lists_used >> list) & 1)
2497 {
2498 MV *mvs = frames[b]->lowresMvs[list][listDist[list]];
2499 int32_t x = mvs[cuIndex].x;
2500 int32_t y = mvs[cuIndex].y;
2501 // NOTE: the dynamic range of abs(x) and abs(y) is 15-bits
2502 displacement += sqrt((double)(abs(x) * abs(x)) + (double)(abs(y) * abs(y)));
2503 }
2504 else
2505 displacement += 0.0;
2506 }
2507 if (lists_used == 3)
2508 displacement = displacement / 2;
2509 qp_adj = pow(displacement, 0.1);
2510 frames[b]->qpAqMotionOffset[cuIndex] = qp_adj;
2511 avg_adj += qp_adj;
2512 avg_adj_pow2 += qp_adj * qp_adj;
2513 }
2514 }
2515 avg_adj /= m_cuCount;
2516 avg_adj_pow2 /= m_cuCount;
2517 sd = sqrt((avg_adj_pow2 - (avg_adj * avg_adj)));
2518 if (sd > 0)
2519 {
2520 for (uint16_t blocky = 0; blocky < m_8x8Height; blocky++)
2521 {
2522 int cuIndex = blocky * strideInCU;
2523 for (uint16_t blockx = 0; blockx < m_8x8Width; blockx++, cuIndex++)
2524 {
2525 qp_adj = frames[b]->qpAqMotionOffset[cuIndex];
2526 qp_adj = (qp_adj - avg_adj) / sd;
2527 if (qp_adj > 1)
2528 {
2529 frames[b]->qpAqOffset[cuIndex] += qp_adj;
2530 frames[b]->qpCuTreeOffset[cuIndex] += qp_adj;
2531 frames[b]->invQscaleFactor[cuIndex] += x265_exp2fix8(qp_adj);
2532 }
2533 }
2534 }
2535 }
2536}
2537
2538void Lookahead::cuTree(Lowres **frames, int numframes, bool bIntra)
2539{
2540 int idx = !bIntra;
2541 int lastnonb, curnonb = 1;
2542 int bframes = 0;
2543
2544 x265_emms();
2545 double totalDuration = 0.0;
2546 for (int j = 0; j <= numframes; j++)
2547 totalDuration += (double)m_param->fpsDenom / m_param->fpsNum;
2548
2549 double averageDuration = totalDuration / (numframes + 1);
2550
2551 int i = numframes;
2552
2553 while (i > 0 && frames[i]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_B)
2554 i--;
2555
2556 lastnonb = i;
2557
2558 /* Lookaheadless MB-tree is not a theoretically distinct case; the same extrapolation could
2559 * be applied to the end of a lookahead buffer of any size. However, it's most needed when
2560 * lookahead=0, so that's what's currently implemented. */
2561 if (!m_param->lookaheadDepth)
2562 {
2563 if (bIntra)
2564 {
2565 memset(frames[0]->propagateCost, 0, m_cuCount * sizeof(uint16_t));
2566 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
2567 memcpy(frames[0]->qpCuTreeOffset, frames[0]->qpAqOffset, m_cuCount * 4 * sizeof(double));
2568 else
2569 memcpy(frames[0]->qpCuTreeOffset, frames[0]->qpAqOffset, m_cuCount * sizeof(double));
2570 return;
2571 }
2572 std::swap(frames[lastnonb]->propagateCost, frames[0]->propagateCost);
2573 memset(frames[0]->propagateCost, 0, m_cuCount * sizeof(uint16_t));
2574 }
2575 else
2576 {
2577 if (lastnonb < idx)
2578 return;
2579 memset(frames[lastnonb]->propagateCost, 0, m_cuCount * sizeof(uint16_t));
2580 }
2581
2582 CostEstimateGroup estGroup(*this, frames);
2583
2584 while (i-- > idx)
2585 {
2586 curnonb = i;
2587 while (frames[curnonb]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_B && curnonb > 0)
2588 curnonb--;
2589
2590 if (curnonb < idx)
2591 break;
2592
2593 estGroup.singleCost(curnonb, lastnonb, lastnonb);
2594
2595 memset(frames[curnonb]->propagateCost, 0, m_cuCount * sizeof(uint16_t));
2596 bframes = lastnonb - curnonb - 1;
2597 if (m_param->bBPyramid && bframes > 1)
2598 {
2599 int middle = (bframes + 1) / 2 + curnonb;
2600 estGroup.singleCost(curnonb, lastnonb, middle);
2601 memset(frames[middle]->propagateCost, 0, m_cuCount * sizeof(uint16_t));
2602 while (i > curnonb)
2603 {
2604 int p0 = i > middle ? middle : curnonb;
2605 int p1 = i < middle ? middle : lastnonb;
2606 if (i != middle)
2607 {
2608 estGroup.singleCost(p0, p1, i);
2609 estimateCUPropagate(frames, averageDuration, p0, p1, i, 0);
2610 }
2611 i--;
2612 }
2613
2614 estimateCUPropagate(frames, averageDuration, curnonb, lastnonb, middle, 1);
2615 }
2616 else
2617 {
2618 while (i > curnonb)
2619 {
2620 estGroup.singleCost(curnonb, lastnonb, i);
2621 estimateCUPropagate(frames, averageDuration, curnonb, lastnonb, i, 0);
2622 i--;
2623 }
2624 }
2625 estimateCUPropagate(frames, averageDuration, curnonb, lastnonb, lastnonb, 1);
2626 lastnonb = curnonb;
2627 }
2628
2629 if (!m_param->lookaheadDepth)
2630 {
2631 estGroup.singleCost(0, lastnonb, lastnonb);
2632 estimateCUPropagate(frames, averageDuration, 0, lastnonb, lastnonb, 1);
2633 std::swap(frames[lastnonb]->propagateCost, frames[0]->propagateCost);
2634 }
2635
2636 cuTreeFinish(frames[lastnonb], averageDuration, lastnonb);
2637 if (m_param->bBPyramid && bframes > 1 && !m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize)
2638 cuTreeFinish(frames[lastnonb + (bframes + 1) / 2], averageDuration, 0);
2639}
2640
2641void Lookahead::estimateCUPropagate(Lowres **frames, double averageDuration, int p0, int p1, int b, int referenced)
2642{
2643 uint16_t *refCosts[2] = { frames[p0]->propagateCost, frames[p1]->propagateCost };
2644 int32_t distScaleFactor = (((b - p0) << 8) + ((p1 - p0) >> 1)) / (p1 - p0);
2645 int32_t bipredWeight = m_param->bEnableWeightedBiPred ? 64 - (distScaleFactor >> 2) : 32;
2646 int32_t bipredWeights[2] = { bipredWeight, 64 - bipredWeight };
2647 int listDist[2] = { b - p0, p1 - b };
2648
2649 memset(m_scratch, 0, m_8x8Width * sizeof(int));
2650
2651 uint16_t *propagateCost = frames[b]->propagateCost;
2652
2653 x265_emms();
2654 double fpsFactor = CLIP_DURATION((double)m_param->fpsDenom / m_param->fpsNum) / CLIP_DURATION(averageDuration);
2655
2656 /* For non-referred frames the source costs are always zero, so just memset one row and re-use it. */
2657 if (!referenced)
2658 memset(frames[b]->propagateCost, 0, m_8x8Width * sizeof(uint16_t));
2659
2660 int32_t strideInCU = m_8x8Width;
2661 for (uint16_t blocky = 0; blocky < m_8x8Height; blocky++)
2662 {
2663 int cuIndex = blocky * strideInCU;
2664 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
2665 primitives.propagateCost(m_scratch, propagateCost,
2666 frames[b]->intraCost + cuIndex, frames[b]->lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b] + cuIndex,
2667 frames[b]->invQscaleFactor8x8 + cuIndex, &fpsFactor, m_8x8Width);
2668 else
2669 primitives.propagateCost(m_scratch, propagateCost,
2670 frames[b]->intraCost + cuIndex, frames[b]->lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b] + cuIndex,
2671 frames[b]->invQscaleFactor + cuIndex, &fpsFactor, m_8x8Width);
2672
2673 if (referenced)
2674 propagateCost += m_8x8Width;
2675
2676 for (uint16_t blockx = 0; blockx < m_8x8Width; blockx++, cuIndex++)
2677 {
2678 int32_t propagate_amount = m_scratch[blockx];
2679 /* Don't propagate for an intra block. */
2680 if (propagate_amount > 0)
2681 {
2682 /* Access width-2 bitfield. */
2683 int32_t lists_used = frames[b]->lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b][cuIndex] >> LOWRES_COST_SHIFT;
2684 /* Follow the MVs to the previous frame(s). */
2685 for (uint16_t list = 0; list < 2; list++)
2686 {
2687 if ((lists_used >> list) & 1)
2688 {
2689#define CLIP_ADD(s, x) (s) = (uint16_t)X265_MIN((s) + (x), (1 << 16) - 1)
2690 int32_t listamount = propagate_amount;
2691 /* Apply bipred weighting. */
2692 if (lists_used == 3)
2693 listamount = (listamount * bipredWeights[list] + 32) >> 6;
2694
2695 MV *mvs = frames[b]->lowresMvs[list][listDist[list]];
2696
2697 /* Early termination for simple case of mv0. */
2698 if (!mvs[cuIndex].word)
2699 {
2700 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][cuIndex], listamount);
2701 continue;
2702 }
2703
2704 int32_t x = mvs[cuIndex].x;
2705 int32_t y = mvs[cuIndex].y;
2706 int32_t cux = (x >> 5) + blockx;
2707 int32_t cuy = (y >> 5) + blocky;
2708 int32_t idx0 = cux + cuy * strideInCU;
2709 int32_t idx1 = idx0 + 1;
2710 int32_t idx2 = idx0 + strideInCU;
2711 int32_t idx3 = idx0 + strideInCU + 1;
2712 x &= 31;
2713 y &= 31;
2714 int32_t idx0weight = (32 - y) * (32 - x);
2715 int32_t idx1weight = (32 - y) * x;
2716 int32_t idx2weight = y * (32 - x);
2717 int32_t idx3weight = y * x;
2718
2719 /* We could just clip the MVs, but pixels that lie outside the frame probably shouldn't
2720 * be counted. */
2721 if (cux < m_8x8Width - 1 && cuy < m_8x8Height - 1 && cux >= 0 && cuy >= 0)
2722 {
2723 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx0], (listamount * idx0weight + 512) >> 10);
2724 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx1], (listamount * idx1weight + 512) >> 10);
2725 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx2], (listamount * idx2weight + 512) >> 10);
2726 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx3], (listamount * idx3weight + 512) >> 10);
2727 }
2728 else /* Check offsets individually */
2729 {
2730 if (cux < m_8x8Width && cuy < m_8x8Height && cux >= 0 && cuy >= 0)
2731 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx0], (listamount * idx0weight + 512) >> 10);
2732 if (cux + 1 < m_8x8Width && cuy < m_8x8Height && cux + 1 >= 0 && cuy >= 0)
2733 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx1], (listamount * idx1weight + 512) >> 10);
2734 if (cux < m_8x8Width && cuy + 1 < m_8x8Height && cux >= 0 && cuy + 1 >= 0)
2735 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx2], (listamount * idx2weight + 512) >> 10);
2736 if (cux + 1 < m_8x8Width && cuy + 1 < m_8x8Height && cux + 1 >= 0 && cuy + 1 >= 0)
2737 CLIP_ADD(refCosts[list][idx3], (listamount * idx3weight + 512) >> 10);
2738 }
2739 }
2740 }
2741 }
2742 }
2743 }
2744
2745 if (m_param->rc.vbvBufferSize && m_param->lookaheadDepth && referenced)
2746 cuTreeFinish(frames[b], averageDuration, b == p1 ? b - p0 : 0);
2747}
2748
2749void Lookahead::computeCUTreeQpOffset(Lowres *frame, double averageDuration, int ref0Distance)
2750{
2751 int fpsFactor = (int)(CLIP_DURATION(averageDuration) / CLIP_DURATION((double)m_param->fpsDenom / m_param->fpsNum) * 256);
2752 uint32_t loopIncr = (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8) ? 8 : 16;
2753
2754 double weightdelta = 0.0;
2755 if (ref0Distance && frame->weightedCostDelta[ref0Distance - 1] > 0)
2756 weightdelta = (1.0 - frame->weightedCostDelta[ref0Distance - 1]);
2757
2758 uint32_t widthFullRes = frame->widthFullRes;
2759 uint32_t heightFullRes = frame->heightFullRes;
2760
2761 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
2762 {
2763 int minAQDepth = frame->pAQLayer->minAQDepth;
2764
2765 PicQPAdaptationLayer* pQPLayerMin = &frame->pAQLayer[minAQDepth];
2766 double* pcCuTree8x8 = pQPLayerMin->dCuTreeOffset8x8;
2767
2768 for (int cuY = 0; cuY < m_8x8Height; cuY++)
2769 {
2770 for (int cuX = 0; cuX < m_8x8Width; cuX++)
2771 {
2772 const int cuXY = cuX + cuY * m_8x8Width;
2773 int intracost = ((frame->intraCost[cuXY] / 4) * frame->invQscaleFactor8x8[cuXY] + 128) >> 8;
2774 if (intracost)
2775 {
2776 int propagateCost = ((frame->propagateCost[cuXY] / 4) * fpsFactor + 128) >> 8;
2777 double log2_ratio = X265_LOG2(intracost + propagateCost) - X265_LOG2(intracost) + weightdelta;
2778
2779 pcCuTree8x8[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4] = log2_ratio;
2780 pcCuTree8x8[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + 1] = log2_ratio;
2781 pcCuTree8x8[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + frame->maxBlocksInRowFullRes] = log2_ratio;
2782 pcCuTree8x8[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + frame->maxBlocksInRowFullRes + 1] = log2_ratio;
2783 }
2784 }
2785 }
2786
2787 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < 4; d++)
2788 {
2789 int ctuSizeIdx = 6 - g_log2Size[m_param->maxCUSize];
2790 int aqDepth = g_log2Size[m_param->maxCUSize] - g_log2Size[m_param->rc.qgSize];
2791 if (!aqLayerDepth[ctuSizeIdx][aqDepth][d])
2792 continue;
2793
2794 PicQPAdaptationLayer* pQPLayer = &frame->pAQLayer[d];
2795 const uint32_t aqPartWidth = pQPLayer->aqPartWidth;
2796 const uint32_t aqPartHeight = pQPLayer->aqPartHeight;
2797
2798 const uint32_t numAQPartInWidth = pQPLayer->numAQPartInWidth;
2799 const uint32_t numAQPartInHeight = pQPLayer->numAQPartInHeight;
2800
2801 double* pcQP = pQPLayer->dQpOffset;
2802 double* pcCuTree = pQPLayer->dCuTreeOffset;
2803
2804 uint32_t maxCols = frame->maxBlocksInRowFullRes;
2805
2806 for (uint32_t y = 0; y < numAQPartInHeight; y++)
2807 {
2808 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < numAQPartInWidth; x++, pcQP++, pcCuTree++)
2809 {
2810 uint32_t block_x = x * aqPartWidth;
2811 uint32_t block_y = y * aqPartHeight;
2812
2813 uint32_t blockXY = 0;
2814 double log2_ratio = 0;
2815 for (uint32_t block_yy = block_y; block_yy < block_y + aqPartHeight && block_yy < heightFullRes; block_yy += loopIncr)
2816 {
2817 for (uint32_t block_xx = block_x; block_xx < block_x + aqPartWidth && block_xx < widthFullRes; block_xx += loopIncr)
2818 {
2819 uint32_t idx = ((block_yy / loopIncr) * (maxCols)) + (block_xx / loopIncr);
2820
2821 log2_ratio += *(pcCuTree8x8 + idx);
2822
2823 blockXY++;
2824 }
2825 }
2826
2827 double qp_offset = (m_cuTreeStrength * log2_ratio) / blockXY;
2828
2829 *pcCuTree = *pcQP - qp_offset;
2830 }
2831 }
2832 }
2833 }
2834 else
2835 {
2836 for (uint32_t d = 0; d < 4; d++)
2837 {
2838 int ctuSizeIdx = 6 - g_log2Size[m_param->maxCUSize];
2839 int aqDepth = g_log2Size[m_param->maxCUSize] - g_log2Size[m_param->rc.qgSize];
2840 if (!aqLayerDepth[ctuSizeIdx][aqDepth][d])
2841 continue;
2842
2843 PicQPAdaptationLayer* pQPLayer = &frame->pAQLayer[d];
2844 const uint32_t aqPartWidth = pQPLayer->aqPartWidth;
2845 const uint32_t aqPartHeight = pQPLayer->aqPartHeight;
2846
2847 const uint32_t numAQPartInWidth = pQPLayer->numAQPartInWidth;
2848 const uint32_t numAQPartInHeight = pQPLayer->numAQPartInHeight;
2849
2850 double* pcQP = pQPLayer->dQpOffset;
2851 double* pcCuTree = pQPLayer->dCuTreeOffset;
2852
2853 uint32_t maxCols = frame->maxBlocksInRow;
2854
2855 for (uint32_t y = 0; y < numAQPartInHeight; y++)
2856 {
2857 for (uint32_t x = 0; x < numAQPartInWidth; x++, pcQP++, pcCuTree++)
2858 {
2859 uint32_t block_x = x * aqPartWidth;
2860 uint32_t block_y = y * aqPartHeight;
2861
2862 uint32_t blockXY = 0;
2863 double log2_ratio = 0;
2864 for (uint32_t block_yy = block_y; block_yy < block_y + aqPartHeight && block_yy < heightFullRes; block_yy += loopIncr)
2865 {
2866 for (uint32_t block_xx = block_x; block_xx < block_x + aqPartWidth && block_xx < widthFullRes; block_xx += loopIncr)
2867 {
2868 uint32_t idx = ((block_yy / loopIncr) * (maxCols)) + (block_xx / loopIncr);
2869
2870 int intraCost = (frame->intraCost[idx] * frame->invQscaleFactor[idx] + 128) >> 8;
2871 int propagateCost = (frame->propagateCost[idx] * fpsFactor + 128) >> 8;
2872
2873 log2_ratio += (X265_LOG2(intraCost + propagateCost) - X265_LOG2(intraCost) + weightdelta);
2874
2875 blockXY++;
2876 }
2877 }
2878
2879 double qp_offset = (m_cuTreeStrength * log2_ratio) / blockXY;
2880
2881 *pcCuTree = *pcQP - qp_offset;
2882
2883 }
2884 }
2885 }
2886 }
2887}
2888
2889void Lookahead::cuTreeFinish(Lowres *frame, double averageDuration, int ref0Distance)
2890{
2891 if (m_param->rc.hevcAq)
2892 {
2893 computeCUTreeQpOffset(frame, averageDuration, ref0Distance);
2894 }
2895 else
2896 {
2897 int fpsFactor = (int)(CLIP_DURATION(averageDuration) / CLIP_DURATION((double)m_param->fpsDenom / m_param->fpsNum) * 256);
2898 double weightdelta = 0.0;
2899
2900 if (ref0Distance && frame->weightedCostDelta[ref0Distance - 1] > 0)
2901 weightdelta = (1.0 - frame->weightedCostDelta[ref0Distance - 1]);
2902
2903 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
2904 {
2905 for (int cuY = 0; cuY < m_8x8Height; cuY++)
2906 {
2907 for (int cuX = 0; cuX < m_8x8Width; cuX++)
2908 {
2909 const int cuXY = cuX + cuY * m_8x8Width;
2910 int intracost = ((frame->intraCost[cuXY]) / 4 * frame->invQscaleFactor8x8[cuXY] + 128) >> 8;
2911 if (intracost)
2912 {
2913 int propagateCost = ((frame->propagateCost[cuXY]) / 4 * fpsFactor + 128) >> 8;
2914 double log2_ratio = X265_LOG2(intracost + propagateCost) - X265_LOG2(intracost) + weightdelta;
2915 frame->qpCuTreeOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4] = frame->qpAqOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4] - m_cuTreeStrength * (log2_ratio);
2916 frame->qpCuTreeOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + 1] = frame->qpAqOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + 1] - m_cuTreeStrength * (log2_ratio);
2917 frame->qpCuTreeOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + frame->maxBlocksInRowFullRes] = frame->qpAqOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + frame->maxBlocksInRowFullRes] - m_cuTreeStrength * (log2_ratio);
2918 frame->qpCuTreeOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + frame->maxBlocksInRowFullRes + 1] = frame->qpAqOffset[cuX * 2 + cuY * m_8x8Width * 4 + frame->maxBlocksInRowFullRes + 1] - m_cuTreeStrength * (log2_ratio);
2919 }
2920 }
2921 }
2922 }
2923 else
2924 {
2925 for (int cuIndex = 0; cuIndex < m_cuCount; cuIndex++)
2926 {
2927 int intracost = (frame->intraCost[cuIndex] * frame->invQscaleFactor[cuIndex] + 128) >> 8;
2928 if (intracost)
2929 {
2930 int propagateCost = (frame->propagateCost[cuIndex] * fpsFactor + 128) >> 8;
2931 double log2_ratio = X265_LOG2(intracost + propagateCost) - X265_LOG2(intracost) + weightdelta;
2932 frame->qpCuTreeOffset[cuIndex] = frame->qpAqOffset[cuIndex] - m_cuTreeStrength * log2_ratio;
2933 }
2934 }
2935 }
2936 }
2937}

2939/* If MB-tree changes the quantizers, we need to recalculate the frame cost without
2940 * re-running lookahead. */
2941int64_t Lookahead::frameCostRecalculate(Lowres** frames, int p0, int p1, int b)
2942{
2943 if (frames[b]->sliceType == X265_TYPE_B)
2944 return frames[b]->costEstAq[b - p0][p1 - b];
2945
2946 int64_t score = 0;
2947 int *rowSatd = frames[b]->rowSatds[b - p0][p1 - b];
2948
2949 x265_emms();
2950
2951 if (m_param->rc.hevcAq)
2952 {
2953 int minAQDepth = frames[b]->pAQLayer->minAQDepth;
2954 PicQPAdaptationLayer* pQPLayer = &frames[b]->pAQLayer[minAQDepth];
2955 double* pcQPCuTree = pQPLayer->dCuTreeOffset;
2956
2957 // Use new qp offset values for qpAqOffset, qpCuTreeOffset and invQscaleFactor buffer
2958 for (int cuy = m_8x8Height - 1; cuy >= 0; cuy--)
2959 {
2960 rowSatd[cuy] = 0;
2961 for (int cux = m_8x8Width - 1; cux >= 0; cux--)
2962 {
2963 int cuxy = cux + cuy * m_8x8Width;
2964 int cuCost = frames[b]->lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b][cuxy] & LOWRES_COST_MASK;
2965 double qp_adj;
2966
2967 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
2968 qp_adj = (pcQPCuTree[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4] +
2969 pcQPCuTree[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4 + 1] +
2970 pcQPCuTree[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4 + frames[b]->maxBlocksInRowFullRes] +
2971 pcQPCuTree[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4 + frames[b]->maxBlocksInRowFullRes + 1]) / 4;
2972 else
2973 qp_adj = *(pcQPCuTree + cuxy);
2974
2975 cuCost = (cuCost * x265_exp2fix8(qp_adj) + 128) >> 8;
2976 rowSatd[cuy] += cuCost;
2977 if ((cuy > 0 && cuy < m_8x8Height - 1 &&
2978 cux > 0 && cux < m_8x8Width - 1) ||
2979 m_8x8Width <= 2 || m_8x8Height <= 2)
2980 {
2981 score += cuCost;
2982 }
2983 }
2984 }
2985 }
2986 else
2987 {
2988 double *qp_offset = frames[b]->qpCuTreeOffset;
2989
2990 for (int cuy = m_8x8Height - 1; cuy >= 0; cuy--)
2991 {
2992 rowSatd[cuy] = 0;
2993 for (int cux = m_8x8Width - 1; cux >= 0; cux--)
2994 {
2995 int cuxy = cux + cuy * m_8x8Width;
2996 int cuCost = frames[b]->lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b][cuxy] & LOWRES_COST_MASK;
2997 double qp_adj;
2998 if (m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
2999 qp_adj = (qp_offset[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4] +
3000 qp_offset[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4 + 1] +
3001 qp_offset[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4 + frames[b]->maxBlocksInRowFullRes] +
3002 qp_offset[cux * 2 + cuy * m_8x8Width * 4 + frames[b]->maxBlocksInRowFullRes + 1]) / 4;
3003 else
3004 qp_adj = qp_offset[cuxy];
3005 cuCost = (cuCost * x265_exp2fix8(qp_adj) + 128) >> 8;
3006 rowSatd[cuy] += cuCost;
3007 if ((cuy > 0 && cuy < m_8x8Height - 1 &&
3008 cux > 0 && cux < m_8x8Width - 1) ||
3009 m_8x8Width <= 2 || m_8x8Height <= 2)
3010 {
3011 score += cuCost;
3012 }
3013 }
3014 }
3015 }
3016
3017 return score;
3018}

3049
3050void CostEstimateGroup::processTasks(int workerThreadID)
3051{
3052 ThreadPool* pool = m_lookahead.m_pool;
3053 int id = workerThreadID;
3054 if (workerThreadID < 0)
3055 id = pool ? pool->m_numWorkers : 0;
3056 LookaheadTLD& tld = m_lookahead.m_tld[id];
3057
3058 m_lock.acquire();
3059 while (m_jobAcquired < m_jobTotal)
3060 {
3061 int i = m_jobAcquired++;
3062 m_lock.release();
3063
3064 if (m_batchMode)
3065 {
3066 ProfileLookaheadTime(tld.batchElapsedTime, tld.countBatches);
3067 ProfileScopeEvent(estCostSingle);
3068
3069 Estimate& e = m_estimates[i];
3070 estimateFrameCost(tld, e.p0, e.p1, e.b, false);
3071 }
3072 else
3073 {
3074 ProfileLookaheadTime(tld.coopSliceElapsedTime, tld.countCoopSlices);
3075 ProfileScopeEvent(estCostCoop);
3076
3077 X265_CHECK(i < MAX_COOP_SLICES, "impossible number of coop slices\n");
3078
3079 int firstY, lastY;
3080 bool lastRow;
3081 if (m_lookahead.m_param->bEnableHME)
3082 {
3083 int numRowsPerSlice = m_lookahead.m_4x4Height / m_lookahead.m_param->lookaheadSlices;
3084 numRowsPerSlice = X265_MIN(X265_MAX(numRowsPerSlice, 5), m_lookahead.m_4x4Height);
3085 firstY = numRowsPerSlice * i;
3086 lastY = (i == m_jobTotal - 1) ? m_lookahead.m_4x4Height - 1 : numRowsPerSlice * (i + 1) - 1;
3087 lastRow = true;
3088 for (int cuY = lastY; cuY >= firstY; cuY--)
3089 {
3090 for (int cuX = m_lookahead.m_4x4Width - 1; cuX >= 0; cuX--)
3091 estimateCUCost(tld, cuX, cuY, m_coop.p0, m_coop.p1, m_coop.b, m_coop.bDoSearch, lastRow, i, 1);
3092 lastRow = false;
3093 }
3094 }
3095
3096 firstY = m_lookahead.m_numRowsPerSlice * i;
3097 lastY = (i == m_jobTotal - 1) ? m_lookahead.m_8x8Height - 1 : m_lookahead.m_numRowsPerSlice * (i + 1) - 1;
3098 lastRow = true;
3099 for (int cuY = lastY; cuY >= firstY; cuY--)
3100 {
3101 m_frames[m_coop.b]->rowSatds[m_coop.b - m_coop.p0][m_coop.p1 - m_coop.b][cuY] = 0;
3102
3103 for (int cuX = m_lookahead.m_8x8Width - 1; cuX >= 0; cuX--)
3104 estimateCUCost(tld, cuX, cuY, m_coop.p0, m_coop.p1, m_coop.b, m_coop.bDoSearch, lastRow, i, 0);
3105
3106 lastRow = false;
3107 }
3108 }
3109
3110 m_lock.acquire();
3111 }
3112 m_lock.release();
3113}
3114
3115int64_t CostEstimateGroup::estimateFrameCost(LookaheadTLD& tld, int p0, int p1, int b, bool bIntraPenalty)
3116{
3117 Lowres* fenc = m_frames[b];
3118 x265_param* param = m_lookahead.m_param;
3119 int64_t score = 0;
3120
3121 if (fenc->costEst[b - p0][p1 - b] >= 0 && fenc->rowSatds[b - p0][p1 - b][0] != -1)
3122 score = fenc->costEst[b - p0][p1 - b];
3123 else
3124 {
3125 bool bDoSearch[2];
3126 bDoSearch[0] = fenc->lowresMvs[0][b - p0][0].x == 0x7FFF;
3127 bDoSearch[1] = p1 > b && fenc->lowresMvs[1][p1 - b][0].x == 0x7FFF;
3128
3129#if CHECKED_BUILD
3130 X265_CHECK(!(p0 < b && fenc->lowresMvs[0][b - p0][0].x == 0x7FFE), "motion search batch duplication L0\n");
3131 X265_CHECK(!(p1 > b && fenc->lowresMvs[1][p1 - b][0].x == 0x7FFE), "motion search batch duplication L1\n");
3132 if (bDoSearch[0]) fenc->lowresMvs[0][b - p0][0].x = 0x7FFE;
3133 if (bDoSearch[1]) fenc->lowresMvs[1][p1 - b][0].x = 0x7FFE;
3134#endif
3135
3136 fenc->weightedRef[b - p0].isWeighted = false;
3137 if (param->bEnableWeightedPred && bDoSearch[0])
3138 tld.weightsAnalyse(*m_frames[b], *m_frames[p0]);
3139
3140 fenc->costEst[b - p0][p1 - b] = 0;
3141 fenc->costEstAq[b - p0][p1 - b] = 0;
3142
3143 if (!m_batchMode && m_lookahead.m_numCoopSlices > 1 && ((p1 > b) || bDoSearch[0] || bDoSearch[1]))
3144 {
3145 /* Use cooperative mode if a thread pool is available and the cost estimate is
3146 * going to need motion searches or bidir measurements */
3147
3148 memset(&m_slice, 0, sizeof(Slice) * m_lookahead.m_numCoopSlices);
3149
3150 m_lock.acquire();
3151 X265_CHECK(!m_batchMode, "single CostEstimateGroup instance cannot mix batch modes\n");
3152 m_coop.p0 = p0;
3153 m_coop.p1 = p1;
3154 m_coop.b = b;
3155 m_coop.bDoSearch[0] = bDoSearch[0];
3156 m_coop.bDoSearch[1] = bDoSearch[1];
3157 m_jobTotal = m_lookahead.m_numCoopSlices;
3158 m_jobAcquired = 0;
3159 m_lock.release();
3160
3161 tryBondPeers(*m_lookahead.m_pool, m_jobTotal);
3162
3163 processTasks(-1);
3164
3165 waitForExit();
3166
3167 for (int i = 0; i < m_lookahead.m_numCoopSlices; i++)
3168 {
3169 fenc->costEst[b - p0][p1 - b] += m_slice[i].costEst;
3170 fenc->costEstAq[b - p0][p1 - b] += m_slice[i].costEstAq;
3171 if (p1 == b)
3172 fenc->intraMbs[b - p0] += m_slice[i].intraMbs;
3173 }
3174 }
3175 else
3176 {
3177 /* Calculate MVs for 1/16th resolution*/
3178 bool lastRow;
3179 if (param->bEnableHME)
3180 {
3181 lastRow = true;
3182 for (int cuY = m_lookahead.m_4x4Height - 1; cuY >= 0; cuY--)
3183 {
3184 for (int cuX = m_lookahead.m_4x4Width - 1; cuX >= 0; cuX--)
3185 estimateCUCost(tld, cuX, cuY, p0, p1, b, bDoSearch, lastRow, -1, 1);
3186 lastRow = false;
3187 }
3188 }
3189 lastRow = true;
3190 for (int cuY = m_lookahead.m_8x8Height - 1; cuY >= 0; cuY--)
3191 {
3192 fenc->rowSatds[b - p0][p1 - b][cuY] = 0;
3193
3194 for (int cuX = m_lookahead.m_8x8Width - 1; cuX >= 0; cuX--)
3195 estimateCUCost(tld, cuX, cuY, p0, p1, b, bDoSearch, lastRow, -1, 0);
3196
3197 lastRow = false;
3198 }
3199 }
3200
3201 score = fenc->costEst[b - p0][p1 - b];
3202
3203 if (b != p1)
3204 score = score * 100 / (130 + param->bFrameBias);
3205
3206 fenc->costEst[b - p0][p1 - b] = score;
3207 }
3208
3209 if (bIntraPenalty)
3210 // arbitrary penalty for I-blocks after B-frames
3211 score += score * fenc->intraMbs[b - p0] / (tld.ncu * 8);
3212
3213 return score;
3214}
3215
3216void CostEstimateGroup::estimateCUCost(LookaheadTLD& tld, int cuX, int cuY, int p0, int p1, int b, bool bDoSearch[2], bool lastRow, int slice, bool hme)
3217{
3218 Lowres *fref0 = m_frames[p0];
3219 Lowres *fref1 = m_frames[p1];
3220 Lowres *fenc = m_frames[b];
3221
3222 ReferencePlanes *wfref0 = fenc->weightedRef[b - p0].isWeighted && !hme ? &fenc->weightedRef[b - p0] : fref0;
3223
3224 const int widthInCU = hme ? m_lookahead.m_4x4Width : m_lookahead.m_8x8Width;
3225 const int heightInCU = hme ? m_lookahead.m_4x4Height : m_lookahead.m_8x8Height;
3226 const int bBidir = (b < p1);
3227 const int cuXY = cuX + cuY * widthInCU;
3228 const int cuXY_4x4 = (cuX / 2) + (cuY / 2) * widthInCU / 2;
3229 const int cuSize = X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE;
3230 const intptr_t pelOffset = cuSize * cuX + cuSize * cuY * (hme ? fenc->lumaStride/2 : fenc->lumaStride);
3231
3232 if ((bBidir || bDoSearch[0] || bDoSearch[1]) && hme)
3233 tld.me.setSourcePU(fenc->lowerResPlane[0], fenc->lumaStride / 2, pelOffset, cuSize, cuSize, X265_HEX_SEARCH, m_lookahead.m_param->hmeSearchMethod[0], m_lookahead.m_param->hmeSearchMethod[1], 1);
3234 else if((bBidir || bDoSearch[0] || bDoSearch[1]) && !hme)
3235 tld.me.setSourcePU(fenc->lowresPlane[0], fenc->lumaStride, pelOffset, cuSize, cuSize, X265_HEX_SEARCH, m_lookahead.m_param->hmeSearchMethod[0], m_lookahead.m_param->hmeSearchMethod[1], 1);
3236
3237
3238 /* A small, arbitrary bias to avoid VBV problems caused by zero-residual lookahead blocks. */
3239 int lowresPenalty = 4;
3240 int listDist[2] = { b - p0, p1 - b};
3241
3242 MV mvmin, mvmax;
3243 int bcost = tld.me.COST_MAX;
3244 int listused = 0;
3245
3246 // TODO: restrict to slices boundaries
3247 // establish search bounds that don't cross extended frame boundaries
3248 mvmin.x = (int32_t)(-cuX * cuSize - 8);
3249 mvmin.y = (int32_t)(-cuY * cuSize - 8);
3250 mvmax.x = (int32_t)((widthInCU - cuX - 1) * cuSize + 8);
3251 mvmax.y = (int32_t)((heightInCU - cuY - 1) * cuSize + 8);
3252
3253 for (int i = 0; i < 1 + bBidir; i++)
3254 {
3255 int& fencCost = hme ? fenc->lowerResMvCosts[i][listDist[i]][cuXY] : fenc->lowresMvCosts[i][listDist[i]][cuXY];
3256 int skipCost = INT_MAX;
3257
3258 if (!bDoSearch[i])
3259 {
3260 COPY2_IF_LT(bcost, fencCost, listused, i + 1);
3261 continue;
3262 }
3263
3264 int numc = 0;
3265 MV mvc[5], mvp;
3266 MV* fencMV = hme ? &fenc->lowerResMvs[i][listDist[i]][cuXY] : &fenc->lowresMvs[i][listDist[i]][cuXY];
3267 ReferencePlanes* fref = i ? fref1 : wfref0;
3268
3269 /* Reverse-order MV prediction */
3270#define MVC(mv) mvc[numc++] = mv;
3271 if (cuX < widthInCU - 1)
3272 MVC(fencMV[1]);
3273 if (!lastRow)
3274 {
3275 MVC(fencMV[widthInCU]);
3276 if (cuX > 0)
3277 MVC(fencMV[widthInCU - 1]);
3278 if (cuX < widthInCU - 1)
3279 MVC(fencMV[widthInCU + 1]);
3280 }
3281 if (fenc->lowerResMvs[0][0] && !hme && fenc->lowerResMvCosts[i][listDist[i]][cuXY_4x4] > 0)
3282 {
3283 MVC((fenc->lowerResMvs[i][listDist[i]][cuXY_4x4]) * 2);
3284 }
3285#undef MVC
3286
3287 if (!numc)
3288 mvp = 0;
3289 else
3290 {
3291 ALIGN_VAR_32(pixel, subpelbuf[X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE * X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE]);
3292 int mvpcost = MotionEstimate::COST_MAX;
3293
3294 /* measure SATD cost of each neighbor MV (estimating merge analysis)
3295 * and use the lowest cost MV as MVP (estimating AMVP). Since all
3296 * mvc[] candidates are measured here, none are passed to motionEstimate */
3297 for (int idx = 0; idx < numc; idx++)
3298 {
3299 intptr_t stride = X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE;
3300 pixel *src = fref->lowresMC(pelOffset, mvc[idx], subpelbuf, stride, hme);
3301 int cost = tld.me.bufSATD(src, stride);
3302 COPY2_IF_LT(mvpcost, cost, mvp, mvc[idx]);
3303 /* Except for mv0 case, everyting else is likely to have enough residual to not trigger the skip. */
3304 if (!mvp.notZero() && bBidir)
3305 skipCost = cost;
3306 }
3307 }
3308
3309 int searchRange = m_lookahead.m_param->bEnableHME ? (hme ? m_lookahead.m_param->hmeRange[0] : m_lookahead.m_param->hmeRange[1]) : s_merange;
3310 /* ME will never return a cost larger than the cost @MVP, so we do not
3311 * have to check that ME cost is more than the estimated merge cost */
3312 if(!hme)
3313 fencCost = tld.me.motionEstimate(fref, mvmin, mvmax, mvp, 0, NULL, searchRange, *fencMV, m_lookahead.m_param->maxSlices);
3314 else
3315 fencCost = tld.me.motionEstimate(fref, mvmin, mvmax, mvp, 0, NULL, searchRange, *fencMV, m_lookahead.m_param->maxSlices, fref->lowerResPlane[0]);
3316 if (skipCost < 64 && skipCost < fencCost && bBidir)
3317 {
3318 fencCost = skipCost;
3319 *fencMV = 0;
3320 }
3321 COPY2_IF_LT(bcost, fencCost, listused, i + 1);
3322 }
3323 if (hme)
3324 return;
3325
3326 if (bBidir) /* B, also consider bidir */
3327 {
3328 /* NOTE: the wfref0 (weightp) is not used for BIDIR */
3329
3330 /* avg(l0-mv, l1-mv) candidate */
3331 ALIGN_VAR_32(pixel, subpelbuf0[X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE * X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE]);
3332 ALIGN_VAR_32(pixel, subpelbuf1[X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE * X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE]);
3333 intptr_t stride0 = X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE, stride1 = X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE;
3334 pixel *src0 = fref0->lowresMC(pelOffset, fenc->lowresMvs[0][listDist[0]][cuXY], subpelbuf0, stride0, 0);
3335 pixel *src1 = fref1->lowresMC(pelOffset, fenc->lowresMvs[1][listDist[1]][cuXY], subpelbuf1, stride1, 0);
3336 ALIGN_VAR_32(pixel, ref[X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE * X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE]);
3337 primitives.pu[LUMA_8x8].pixelavg_pp[NONALIGNED](ref, X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE, src0, stride0, src1, stride1, 32);
3338 int bicost = tld.me.bufSATD(ref, X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE);
3339 COPY2_IF_LT(bcost, bicost, listused, 3);
3340 /* coloc candidate */
3341 src0 = fref0->lowresPlane[0] + pelOffset;
3342 src1 = fref1->lowresPlane[0] + pelOffset;
3343 primitives.pu[LUMA_8x8].pixelavg_pp[NONALIGNED](ref, X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE, src0, fref0->lumaStride, src1, fref1->lumaStride, 32);
3344 bicost = tld.me.bufSATD(ref, X265_LOWRES_CU_SIZE);
3345 COPY2_IF_LT(bcost, bicost, listused, 3);
3346 bcost += lowresPenalty;
3347 }
3348 else /* P, also consider intra */
3349 {
3350 bcost += lowresPenalty;
3351
3352 if (fenc->intraCost[cuXY] < bcost)
3353 {
3354 bcost = fenc->intraCost[cuXY];
3355 listused = 0;
3356 }
3357 }
3358
3359 /* do not include edge blocks in the frame cost estimates, they are not very accurate */
3360 const bool bFrameScoreCU = (cuX > 0 && cuX < widthInCU - 1 &&
3361 cuY > 0 && cuY < heightInCU - 1) || widthInCU <= 2 || heightInCU <= 2;
3362 int bcostAq;
3363 if (m_lookahead.m_param->rc.qgSize == 8)
3364 bcostAq = (bFrameScoreCU && fenc->invQscaleFactor) ? ((bcost * fenc->invQscaleFactor8x8[cuXY] + 128) >> 8) : bcost;
3365 else
3366 bcostAq = (bFrameScoreCU && fenc->invQscaleFactor) ? ((bcost * fenc->invQscaleFactor[cuXY] +128) >> 8) : bcost;
3367
3368 if (bFrameScoreCU)
3369 {
3370 if (slice < 0)
3371 {
3372 fenc->costEst[b - p0][p1 - b] += bcost;
3373 fenc->costEstAq[b - p0][p1 - b] += bcostAq;
3374 if (!listused && !bBidir)
3375 fenc->intraMbs[b - p0]++;
3376 }
3377 else
3378 {
3379 m_slice[slice].costEst += bcost;
3380 m_slice[slice].costEstAq += bcostAq;
3381 if (!listused && !bBidir)
3382 m_slice[slice].intraMbs++;
3383 }
3384 }
3385
3386 fenc->rowSatds[b - p0][p1 - b][cuY] += bcostAq;
3387 fenc->lowresCosts[b - p0][p1 - b][cuXY] = (uint16_t)(X265_MIN(bcost, LOWRES_COST_MASK) | (listused << LOWRES_COST_SHIFT));
3388}
3389
3390}
